title: spicy goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, green pepper, garlic salt and pepper.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Add to cooked noodles.
Pour in tomatoes and tomato sauce and simmer.

title: perfect fudge a-la marie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in heavy pan.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat. Continue boiling, without stirring, until candy thermometer reaches 232°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts. Mix vigorously.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares when cool.
May garnish with pecan half.
Great fudge.

title: mimi's buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour batter in pan and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes, then cut into pieces and remove all of cake from pan (if using a metal pan).
Transfer cut pieces to a serving or cake platter.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Sift flour. Cut butter in flour and mix in sour cream.
Mix well and drop from tablespoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 50 small biscuits.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cup sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and cream of tartar.
Mix thoroughly and put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut; roll in cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar mixed together.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: microwavable peanut brittle
directions: In a glass (1 1/2 quart) bowl, mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir, then 4 minutes more. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave for 2 more minutes.
Stir in soda, then pour in a greased cookie sheet.
Spread and let cool.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown and drain ground beef. Make rice mix according to directions, except substitute tomato sauce for water. If not enough tomato sauce, finish up with water.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Add salt, baking powder and flour slowly until well mixed.
Add cocoa last. Mix at high speed until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done when checked with a toothpick.

title: chocolate malted milk
directions: Pour milk, chocolate syrup and malted milk powder into blender container.
Cover and blend until frothy, about 15 seconds.
Add the ice cream while motor is running.
Blend only until mixed. Yields about 3 cups.

title: corn dogs
directions: Boil frankfurters.
Mix all other ingredients.
Dip frankfurters in batter and cook in deep fat until brown.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers.
Make pudding per package directions. In glass punch bowl or truffle bowl, layer as follows:
1 cake layer, 1/2 pudding mix, 1/2 of each of the fruits, 1/2 of the whipped cream, 2nd cake layer, remaining pudding, remaining fruits, remaining whipped cream and top with crushed nuts.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture, mixing well. Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place in lightly greased mini muffin pan.
Shape balls into a shell by pressing thumb in center.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately place peanut butter cup in center of hot crust.
Cool before removing from pan.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together and cook slowly until golden hard-cracked brown. Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Mix well.
While foaming, spread on buttered cookie sheet.
When it is hard, break into pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix dip ingredients with mixer until smooth. Chill.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches, building up a 1/2-inch edge.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy. Pour over hot crust.
Bake about 25 minutes longer or just until no imprint remains when touched lightly in center.
Cool; cut in squares.
Makes 25 cookies.

title: louisianian creole rice(dirty rice)
directions: To heated cooking oil, add chopped onions, celery and shallots. Saute until soft, at least 10 minutes.
Add chopped or ground livers, ground beef, parsley and garlic.
After browning meat thoroughly, add other liquids.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add to rice and mix well.
Good with beef or fowl.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, white sugar and powdered sugar.
Beat together eggs and salt separately and add.
Add oil and vanilla. Sift together remaining ingredients and add to mixture.

title: stewed apples
directions: Place apples in
a
pot.
Add
water,
sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, flavor and butter.
Over a medium fire, cook for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
A nice after meal dessert. Serves 6 to 8.

title: gooey gob
directions: In frying pan, put hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion and celery.
When done, drain off grease.
Make white sauce (recipe in book).
Add mushroom soup and cheese.
Serve hamburger gravy over rice or potatoes.
Top with Chinese noodles.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add 1 cup salad oil, beating on low speed constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon of grated onion and 1 teaspoon of celery seed.
Mix well; refrigerate until needed.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Bake crust and cool.
Scald cream; mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Slowly add scalded cream.
Cool in a double boiler until thickened.
Add softened gelatin.
Mix a little hot custard with gelatin first.
Divide the custard.
To one portion, add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining custard and 4 stiffly beaten egg whites, that have had 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar beaten into them.
Add rum to taste; spread chocolate custard over crust.
Chill and top with other custard.
Chill until set.
Before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: e~z banana cream pie
directions: Line pie crust with thinly sliced bananas.
Mix sour cream and instant pudding thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill. Top with whip cream as you serve.

title: three bean bake
directions: Cook bacon on sheet pan in oven.
Drain.
Dice or crumble. Cook ground beef and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, to beef and bacon.
Mix carefully.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until hot and bubbling.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and extract.
Add 2 egg yolks. Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternate by adding flour and strawberries to creamed mixture, starting and ending with flour. Beat 2 egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into greased and waxed paper loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean in a 350° oven.

title: no noodle tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk in small casserole dish and mix thoroughly.
Add tuna, 1 cup potato chips and peas; stir well. Sprinkle top with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: princess chicken
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons each of cornstarch and soy sauce; stir well.
Add chicken, mixing well.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Combine next 5 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
Pour peanut oil around top of preheated wok; allow to heat at high (350°) for 1 minute.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons dripping in wok. Heat at medium-high (325°) for 30 seconds.
Add red peppers and stir-fry until dark brown.
Add ginger root and chicken; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add rice wine mixture.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in peanuts.

title: leta's crab dip
directions: Place cream cheese in center of serving dish.
Drain crab meat very well and pour on top of cream cheese (may have to pat and mold to cream cheese block).
Pour about 3/4 bottle of cocktail sauce over cream cheese and crab meat.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat to lukewarm in a double boiler the milk and sugar. Slowly add the eggs.
Cook over low heat and stir constantly until the back of a wooden spoon is coated, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add your favorite seasoning.
(If mixture is lumpy, the custard has cooked too rapidly.
Put into blender and blend until smooth.)

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl combine oats, whole wheat flour, sugar, salt and margarine.
Pour boiling water over all and mix well.
When mixture is cooled to lukewarm, stir in yeast.
Stir in approximately half of flour.
Turn onto floured surface and knead in remaining flour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add dry to wet, alternating with the zucchini.
Bake 1 large loaf for 55 minutes or 3 small loaves for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chile-rice cheesebake(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook rice in water.
Saute onions in butter, remove from heat and stir in salt and half and half.
Set aside.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of rice, cheese, chilies, onion sauce and sour cream.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
May be made in advance and refrigerated until baking time.

title: boy scout dinner
directions: Spray 4 large pieces of aluminum foil with Pam.
Divide beef into 4 patties.
Layer beef patty, vegetables, salt and pepper in center of foil pieces.
Top with pat of butter.
Wrap foil around and secure edges.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can be grilled over coals.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cornflake crumbs, cheese and salt in a large Baggie.
Dip potatoes in melted butter and coat with crumbs.
Place potatoes in lightly greased baking pan. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serve with extra butter and sour cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and oil.
Add eggs, cheese, jalapenos, onion and corn; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Cool 30 minutes before cutting.
Cornbread will be heavier than regular cornbread.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk together (beat).
Add to dry ingredients in saucepan.
Stir and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Then add oleo and vanilla.
Stir until blended. Pour into baked 9-inch pie crust.
Cool; serve with Cool Whip.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat until light and creamy.
Add flour and buttermilk. Beat 2 minutes more.
In small bowl, mix cocoa, soda and hot water.
Add to rest of batter.
Put in 3 (8-inch) pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Fill with Sour Cream Filling and frost with Glossy Chocolate Frosting.

title: zelma's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a loaf in baking dish.
Spread ketchup on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: turtle bars
directions: Place cake mix, butter (melted) and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in large bowl.
Beat at high speed until well mixed.
Place 1/2 the chocolate cake mix in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and press well into bottom.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes and cool.

title: molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in water.
Cool and add cottage cheese, mayo and pineapple
with juice and lemon juice.	Whip milk and add last.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all together, except jello.
Sprinkle the jello over and fold into salad.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onion and salt and leave overnight in refrigerator.
In the morning, rinse and drain well.
Put in a large pan with peppers, vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed and turmeric.
Cook until tender, then add cornstarch dissolved in water.
Add to mixture and boil 5 minutes.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: mini cheesecake(serves 24)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press equal portions onto bottom of 24 lightly greased or paper cup lined muffin cups.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amount of mixture (about 3 tablespoons) into cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until set. Cool.
Chill.
Top with filling.
Refrigerate.

title: lo-fat french toast
directions: Lightly oil a nonstick pan (skillet) and beat on medium heat. Lightly beat together egg whites and applesauce by hand.
Soak each slice of bread on both sides.
Brown bread in nonstick skillet on both sides.
Top each slice with 1 teaspoon strawberry jam.
One gm. fat per serving.

title: plain pastry for pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add shortening.
Mix with hands until shortening is coated.
Add water, distributing evenly.
Use just enough water so particles stick together.
Divide into two balls.
Sprinkle flour on board.
Roll into crust.
Add fruit. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy, about 10 minutes on medium speed on the mixer.
Add flavoring.
Stir flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture beating well after each addition. Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Pour into 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out.
Cool on rack.
Frost with Pineapple Cake Icing.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Drain the pineapple, saving juice to pour over cake layers. Mix margarine, flour, sugar and egg in saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Add pineapple and cook until thick.
Cool for 5 minutes before icing cake.

title: old fashioned nut brittle
directions: In a large heavy saucepan or skillet, stir sugar, corn syrup and 2 cups of water over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking without stirring until 238° on candy thermometer, about 15 minutes.
Add nuts.
Continue cooking until syrup turns golden to 300°, about 20 minutes.
Add butter and soda.
Stir until well blended.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break in pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 1/2 pounds.

title: lingonberry catsup
directions: *Note:
Ten 1-pound cans of whole cranberries or 10 (1-pound) bags of frozen may be used in any combination to taste.

title: curry chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken breasts, then shred. Blend together soup, mayonnaise and curry.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole, layer first with broccoli and shredded chicken.
Top with soup mixture, then layer with Cheddar cheese.
In small pan, melt butter and add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until completely heated.

title: batter rolls
directions: Dissolve
teaspoon sugar in warm water.
Sprinkle in yeast. Let
stand
10 minutes; then stir well.
Combine milk, 1/4
cup sugar,
shortening and salt in saucepan.
Heat until lukewarm
and shortening is melted.
Stir well.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add
cups
flour
and beat vigorously with a wooden spoon or electric mixer until smooth (about 3 minutes). Gradually stir in remaining 1 cup flour.
Batter will be soft. Cover with a tea towel.
Let rise in a warm place (75° to 85°) until
double, about 1 hour.
Stir down dough and let stand 10 minutes.
Fill greased muffin
cups
1/2 full.
Let rise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes. Bake
at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn out
of pans immediately.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: seasoned sirloin steak
directions: Sprinkle both sides of steak with above seasoning.
Place on hot grill for about 5-6 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin slices.
Serve with baked potato and grilled veggies.

title: old fashion butter roll
directions: Make a rich biscuit dough, pinching off enough to roll out

a thin round about the size of a saucer. In the middle of this rounded dough put about 2. Tbsp butter, 2 tsp. sugar and sprinkle cannamon and nutmeg and roll over. Make as many of these needed to fill a large baking pan. Pour the rolls a mixture of 1 1/2 c. milk and 1/2 c. sugar. Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350 degrees until done and brown. Mix the sauce.

title: beef ribs
directions: Place ribs in a pan.
Place remaining ingredients on top. Cook in slow oven about 2 hours at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Place onion, green pepper and celery in blender and blend well.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and celery seed in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Combine all and let stand 24 hours.
Will freeze well.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Add hot water to jello.
While jello is still hot, add cranberry sauce; let cool for about 20 minutes.
Add nuts, pineapple and celery.
Chill until firm.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until lightly brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup blending well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 hour.
When cool, break pieces and stove in a tight container.
(If raw peanuts are used, add 1/8 teaspoon salt to sugar and syrup mixture, before microwaving.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Combine chicken with water to cover in large saucepan.
Cook until chicken is very tender.
Drain and reserve 3 to 4 cups of chicken stock.
Chop chicken, discarding bones and skin.

title: iowa corn casserole
directions: Combine corn mix, corn, egg and milk and put in a long baking dish.
Dice onion and saute in margarine.
Combine onion and margarine, sour cream, salt, dill seed and 1/4 cup cheese.
Mix and put on top of mixture in baking dish like frosting.
Pour rest of cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix
Kool-Aid
as directed.
Pour into a large container and add pineapple juice.
Mix well.
This is better if made the day before
and
let
stand
in
the refrigerator overnight.
I freeze some of
the
mixture in small bowls or ice trays to use in the punch bowl.

title: german hot potato salad with bacon
directions: Scrub potatoes; rinse.
Boil in jackets; let cool.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook bacon in hot pan until crisp.
Add onion; stir and cook until transparent.
Add vinegar, stock or bouillon and seasonings.
Stir and let come to a boil.
Stir in egg; remove from heat and pour over potatoes.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Cook rice as normal.
Saute onions and cook shrimp in oil for about 5 minutes, or until shrimp is pink.
Add eggs; stir constantly until mixed.
Add soy sauce, rice and mushrooms. Slowly add water; simmer.

title: baked hash brown casserole
directions: Pour 1/2 cup melted oleo over thawed potatoes; mix other ingredients except the corn flakes and remaining oleo.
Mix with potatoes thoroughly.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish. Mix the remaining oleo with the crushed corn flakes and spread over the top of the potatoes.
This dish may be fixed in the morning and refrigerated.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine the flour with baking powder, salt and mace and sift together 2 times.
Cream butter in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Add the sugar slowly and beat until mixture resembles whipped cream.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in half the flour mixture, then add flavorings and remaining flour mixture.

title: banana surprise
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes (let cool).
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Mix 2 small packages instant pudding with 3 cups milk.
Pour onto top of last layer.
Slice bananas onto top of pudding layer.
Next, add remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (1/4 cup).

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except green peppers and onions and place in a skillet and simmer for 1 hour.
Next add green peppers and onions.
Cook for 5 more minutes.

title: sugar free tapioca pudding
directions: *Or use 1/4 cup egg substitute.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs.
Add one egg at a time. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Use tube pan.
Top with 1 cup confectioners sugar mixed with lemon juice.

title: slaw
directions: Mix and put in jar.
Refrigerate.
This makes a large amount but will keep for a long time.

title: chicken paprikas(czirkepaprikas)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in shortening. Add seasonings and chicken. Saute about 10 minutes. Add water (2 cups) and simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to liquid.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix flour and remaining water as for thickening gravy.
Add to liquid.
Add dumplings.
Arrange chicken on top.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
Serves 4.

title: santangelo's own pumpkin cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, blend together the cream cheese, eggs, flour and sugar.
Add the pumpkin, heavy cream (unwhipped), vanilla and pie spice.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Without opening the oven, turn the oven temperature to 275° and bake the cheese cake for an additional hour.
Cool in oven for 2 to 3 hours without opening the oven.
Refrigerate.
(The restaurant serves 12 portions from this recipe, but it can make 16 servings.)
Enjoy!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour into bowl with other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Lightly beat egg and add with buttermilk to flour mixture.
Stir until all flour is dampened, then turn out onto lightly floured board or countertop.
Knead 5 to 10 turns (the less kneading the better).
Roll out to desired thickness (3/4-inch is good) and cut into biscuits with floured cutter.
Place in ungreased baking pans or cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine first; then the rest of ingredients.
Pour in raw crusts and cook at 350° or until done. (When a knife blade comes out clean when stuck in center of pie.) Makes 2 pies.

title: sweet potato roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients but egg whites and buttered cracker crumbs
and fold whites in last.
Bake, in buttered casserole, topped with buttered cracker crumbs, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican egg dish
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until firm (about 10 minutes).
Chop and cook green peppers, onions and sausage until done.
Pour picante sauce over eggs, then add green pepper-sausage mixture. Grate cheeses over eggs.
Put back into oven until cheeses are melted.

title: bantam bambi bake
directions: Combine ingredients except nuts.
Marinate venison for 2 days in refrigerator, turning frequently.
Cook as you would lamb. Cover with nuts for last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: diet soup
directions: Cook all together.
If you have a little hamburger or stew meat, you can use that as it gives something to chew on.
This is real skinny soup.
Tastes good, too.

title: crab au gratin - a la betsy
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Gradually blend in half and half.
Add well beaten egg yolks, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, until slightly thickened.
Put crab meat in a large bowl; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Pour mixture from skillet over crab meat; mix well.
Pour into a large casserole sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Stir cocoa and flour together and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Press into greased and floured baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small, bite size pieces.
Combine with other ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: key lime pie
directions: Bake graham cracker crust in a 300° oven for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.
Separate 3 eggs.
Beat yolks.
Set aside whites.
Add condensed milk and stir.
Squeeze limes.
Add to mixture and stir.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into Key lime mixture.
Pour mixture into baked shell.
Bake in a slow oven (250°) for 1 hour until set.
Bake in a 300° oven for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: bambinos
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread crackers with catsup.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place one pepperoni slice on each cracker.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and red pepper over shrimp; set aside. Saute onion and celery in butter in a large skillet until tender. Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add cornstarch, tomato paste and shrimp to vegetables; stir well.
Cook 10 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add green onion and parsley; simmer 5 minutes, stirring often.
Spoon over hot rice in individual serving bowls.

title: teri's caesar salad
directions: Wash lettuce and tear into pieces.
Combine garlic, lemon juice, oil, mustard and pepper; shake well.
(Chill dressing if desired.)
Place lettuce in salad bowl and add croutons and cheese.
Pour dressing over lettuce and toss lightly.
May sprinkle each serving with additional cheese.

title: beef tips napoli
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch cubes; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown in oil in large skillet.
Mix tomato paste with 1 1/2 cups water, lemon juice, sugar, marjoram, carrot and garlic; pour over beef.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours, adding water and salt if needed.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well.
Mix with cheese and parsley.
Serve beef mixture over macaroni.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Wash bean sprouts and crisp.
Place all ingredients in large casserole dish, layering first, green beans, soup, bean sprouts, mushrooms and cheese, repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle onions on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot; heat well, stirring constantly. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Cut top off bread and hollow out.
Mix other ingredients and put in bread.
Wrap in foil and bake 1 hour at 250° or 300°.
Use inside of bread for dipping.
Also may use large Fritos Chips.

title: nut crisp cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven. Flatten with glass that has been dipped in sugar.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use as a marinade.
Pour over meat, refrigerating for 1 to 1 1/2 days.
May be then broiled in oven, but best cooked on grill.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat on bottom of greased pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs with mixer until no lumps.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.
Cut when cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar and 2 cups flour.
Mix with wooden spoon until blended.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender and blend 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour over hot baked crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pork chops and onion soup
directions: Roll pork chops in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour soup over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: minnesota hot dish
directions: Cook all ingredients separate.
When done, mix together.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine ingredients, serve at once.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well together.
Chill.
Serve with celery sticks, carrot sticks, cauliflowerets, broccoli and your favorite snack crackers.

title: jello 'n fruit layers
directions: Add the Jell-O to the boiling water and stir until dissolved. Mix 1 cup cold orange juice and ice to make 1 1/4 cups and stir into the gelatin. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Remove 1 1/2 cups of the gelatin; stir in drained fruit cocktail. Set aside. Stir 1/2 of Cool Whip into remaining Jell-O with wire whisk until blended. Pour into 9-inch square dish. Refrigerate about 10 minutes until set but not firm. Carefully spoon fruited gelatin over creamy layer in dish. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into squares. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Yield: 9 servings.

title: brown edge cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, flour and vanilla. Mix well. Drop about 1/2 teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes at 350° until edges are golden brown.
Cool good.
Keep in airtight container.

title: special oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; beat eggs and lemon extract.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oatmeal and pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: fudge chip cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: no stirring peach cobbler
directions: In shallow oblong pan, melt butter. Put flour, sugar and milk on top of butter. Do Not Stir. Pour peaches over batter and butter. Do Not Stir. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Steam rice; melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion; add beef and brown, then drain.
Season with salt and paprika.
Place in greased baking dish 1/3 of rice and 1/2 of meat.
Sprinkle over half of celery and pepper.
Repeat process.
Place last of rice on top. Pour tomato soup over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour. Serves 6.

title: cheesy garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as you normally do or use leftover mashed potatoes.
Mix in garlic powder, parsley flakes, onion powder and sour cream.
Blend well and spoon into baking dish sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
This is great to spice up leftover mashed potatoes!

title: old fashioned christmas aroma
directions: Bring to boil in pan and let simmer as long as needed to perfume house.
May be used more than once.

title: pear bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and oil and beat.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and mix well.
Fold in nuts. Bake in 2 loaf pans 1 hour at 350°.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Grind liver. (I use blender.)
Cream butter with salt and egg. Add balance of ingredients; mix into a stiff dough.
Form into balls, each the size of a walnut.
Test dough by boiling just one dumpling at first to make sure it does not fall apart; if dough is not thick enough to adhere, add more bread crumbs.
Simmer dumplings 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with soup.

title: coconut pecan icing
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter. Cook 5 minutes. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses; beat in egg. Add milk. Sift together
dry
ingredients.
Stir into molasses mixture. Add vanilla.
Knead
on
lightly
floured board; roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and place
on greased pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: aunt gail's lemon jello
directions: Take 1/2 of the jar of cherries and cut into quarters.
Place in a one cup measuring cup.
Completely fill the cup with boiling water until full.
Put in a small bowl and add 1 small package of lemon jello.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, vanilla, oil and zucchini. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Cut the hot dogs the long way, but not all the way through. The hot dog should open and close like a hinge when done.
Lay the dogs on a baking sheet with cut surfaces exposed.
Line the inside of the hot dogs with mashed potatoes.
Cut the cheese into strips and lay them on top of the mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and nutmeg.
Add parsley, bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9 X 13 casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes (325° if using glass pan).
Let stand a few minutes before serving. Serves 6-8 generously.

title: minted grapefruit leg of lamb
directions: Arrange vegetables over bottom of roasting pan.
Rub lamb with salt and pepper.
Place on top of vegetables.
Pour grapefruit juice mixed with mint over lamb.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, basting every 15 minutes with pan drippings.
Serve with strained pan drippings.

title: snakebite's chicken #2
directions: The ingredients make enough for 2.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the mayonnaise with the buttermilk, lemon juice, parsley and garlic.

title: white potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water.
Whip the potatoes.
Add butter, salt, sugar, vanilla, juice, nutmeg, egg yolks and milk. Blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into potato mixture.
Pour equal amounts into pastry shells and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
If they brown too quickly, put a sheet of tinfoil over the pies during the last few minutes of baking.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour pudding into pie crust. Chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: 7-up barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to ground beef.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: tuscan bruschetta
directions: Cut baguettes into 1/4 inch slices diagonally.
Lightly brush bread with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil and toast under broiler or over hot coals. Set aside.
Combine olives, 6 whole garlic cloves, capers, lemon juice, oil and pepper in a food processor or blender.
Process until finely chopped. Spread a thin layer of olive mixture on each piece of bread.
Garnish with sliced cherry tomatoes and parsley, if desired.
Serves 24.

title: cleaning solution
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good for cleaning walls and most any other surfaces.

title: chicken pie
directions: Spray a long baking dish with Pam.
Place cooked chicken (cut up into small pieces) in dish.
Mix 1 can of soup with 1 can of chicken broth.
Mix Bisquick mix with milk; spread over chicken. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice the Twinkies lengthwise.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with them (filling side up).
Dissolve the Jell-O in the cup of boiling water.
Add the 7-Up.
Add the mixture to the softened ice cream.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in the well drained pineapple.
Pour over the layer of Twinkies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs until well blended.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon; sift into the first mixture.
Fold in the fruit and nuts.
Pour into two large greased loaf pans or 3 or 4 smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken and Veg-All in casserole dish.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, margarine and milk and pour over chicken. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: stove top bass
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Salt and pepper fish.
Add fish to pan. Cook 2 minutes on each side.
Add cut-up tomatoes, pepper and onions.
Add small amount of water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 4 minutes or until vegetables are desired tenderness.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: creamy apple-cabbage slaw(serves 100)
directions: Mix sour cream and seasonings.
Chill.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Lightly mix cabbage with apples.
Pour sour cream mixture over cabbage mixture just before serving.
Toss lightly.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9x13 or larger pan. Sprinkle the coconut evenly in the bottom of the pan. Layer the chopped nuts on top of the coconut. After mixing the cake mix according to the cake directions on the box, put the batter on top of the coconuts and nuts.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 40 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: oven french toast
directions: Mix eggs and orange juice and dip in the bread. Place bread in the pan and sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over the top. Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread (I put in the refrigerator overnight). Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: thelma's chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown chicken.
Remove and add celery and green pepper. Saute.
Add remaining ingredients in large pan and add meat. Simmer 4 to 6 hours.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cut meat into 1/8-inch slices.
Heat oil and butter.
Saute onion.
Add garlic and flour; mix well.
Add broth, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Add meat; cover and cook 20 minutes. Stir in parsley.
Place stew in buttered dish.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Rub sides and bottom of fondue pot with cut garlic.
Add wine and heat slowly until bubbles form and rise to surface.
Combine cheeses, cornstarch and mustard, a spoonful at a time, stirring slowly and continuously into a smooth sauce.
(Stir in a figure eight.)
Add Kirsch (brandy), one tablespoon at a time (1/2 jigger) and again bring to slow boil.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: In top of a large double boiler set over simmering water, melt butter (cut into pieces) with cocoa powder, stirring.
Cook the mixture until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugar and eggs; stir in flour, walnuts, vanilla and salt, combining the mixture well.
Spread the mixture evenly into a well-buttered baking pan, 13 x 9-inch, and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix yellow cake mix as directed. Place 1 teaspoon of cake batter into small greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake until light brown, approximately 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
While hot, dip each one in the mixture of confectioners sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cool on waxed paper.
Top with confectioners sugar rosettes with green leaves.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Mix together all ingredients, saving some cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, milk and oil; then add the rest and mix well.
You can make all at one time, then refrigerate or freeze and pop in microwave for a fast breakfast any time later.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on package. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake when done. Mix pineapple and sugar.
Pour over cake and cool.
Prepare pudding according to directions on package.
Top cake with pudding, Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for several days.

title: fajita burrito
directions: Brown 1/2 onion with ground meat in oil.
Season with dry fajita seasoning, salt and pepper.
Saute remainder of onion and pepper until crunchy (do not overcook).
Butter tortillas and microwave 10 seconds.
Fill with the ingredients and roll together.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Combine and press into shape of pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix 1st four ingredients until smooth. Follow directions on yellow cake mix to make cake batter. Pour cake mix into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan. Slowly spoon cheese mixture over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or slightly longer. Top will become brown.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and cayenne red pepper together.
Mix sifted ingredients with cheese, pecans and margarine.
Shape into rolls and chill.
Slice not quite 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Chill mixture may be stored in refrigerator.

title: deer tips
directions: Put deer meat in a bowl and add parsley, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, garlic powder and wine.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Put flour into a gallon size Ziploc bag.
Drain deer meat and save the liquid.
Put chunks of meat into the bag.
Close the bag and shake to coat meat well. Take meat out of the flour.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and add green peppers, onion and deer meat.
Cook meat until it is brown.
Add water to liquid that was saved and pour into skillet. Add mushrooms at this time.
Simmer over low heat until liquid thickens.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Put into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Microwave popcorn as per the directions.
While it is popping, put Parkay, sugar and caramels in a small saucepan, melting sugar and Parkay before adding caramels.
Stir until the caramels are melted.
Open microwaved popcorn and pour into a container sprayed with nonstick spray.
Be careful that no uncooked kernels go into container.
Pour caramel mixture over popcorn covering the top of all the corn.
Shake it around a little to distribute the caramel. Good snack for bedtime.
Be careful when eating it at first because it will stay hot for a little while.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 18 to 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk to boiling.
Slightly beat eggs, sugar and vanilla; add milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add rice, nutmeg and cinnamon. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes (or until knife comes out clean).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat to boiling.
Pour over ribs or any other meat you wish barbecued.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Stir together (do not beat) egg, brown sugar and vanilla. Quickly stir in flour, soda and salt.
Blend in walnuts, coarsely chopped.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Top will be lightly browned but soft in center when taken from oven.
Cool in pan.
Then cut.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in long baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 400° until knife inserted in it will come out clean.
While cake is cooking, mix your topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Set oven at 375 degrees.
Beat eggs slightly in a 2 qt. bowl. Stir in sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Stir in pecans and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake near center of oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.
May look soft in center but will become firm when cool.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Microwave 1 cup rice, 1 cup water and 1 teaspoon margarine. Mix ground beef and onion.
Nuke 2 minutes; stir and nuke 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Also can use Accent or Season-All.

title: kay's stir-fry
directions: Slice, chop or dice
vegetables.
Cut meat into strips. Preheat stir-fry pan.
Coat pan
with cooking oil and 1 tablespoon margarine.	Saute garlic, onion
and carrots.
Add meat, stirring frequently.
Add
spices
and vegetables.
Cook until meat is browned and vegetables
are tender.
Add soy sauce, if desired, minutes before removing from pan.
Serve over rice.

title: smoky bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Blend well. Heat on Full power for 4 to 6 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking time; serve warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together eggs and milk.
In skillet or saucepan, cook sweet potatoes until it looks dry or caramelized, then add sugar and spices.
Pour hot mixture slowly into eggs and milk, using electric beaters to blend this together, using a low speed to cut back on splattering.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into raw pie shell. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until it tests done.
This pie is never watery.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and soup.
Stir.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and powdered sugar. Cut butter in until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, baking powder, lemon juice and remaining 3 tablespoons flour; mix well.
Pour over baked crust; bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: aunt dump's teacakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: On bottom layer, spread nuts and coconut.
For second layer, mix the cake mix and pour on bottom layer.
Mix together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and butter for third layer.
Drop by spoonfuls onto second layer.
Bake in long pan for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn ball
directions: Put sugar, syrup and butter in saucepan.
When it boils, add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Shape into balls.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake for 30 minutes,
then
top
with drained pineapple slices and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: chef's salad
directions: Tear greens into bite size pieces. Toss greens with onion, celery, meat and cheese. Just before serving toss with dressing. I also like to use a mixture of more than one king of meat and cheddar cheese, along with the swiss cheese. Hard boiled eggs and ripe olives are also good in this recipe.
tags: thin strips of cold cooked meat

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and chili powder very well. Shape into ball, roll in toasted pecans and chili powder on wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days before serving.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Heat first 3 items until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Combine all vegetables and pour vinegar mix over them.
Cover and refrigerate. Good after sets 24 hours and will keep 10 to 14 days.
Serves 16 (2 quarts).

title: mall chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Mix dry ingredients. Add together, then add vanilla and chocolate chips. Mix well.

Spoon onto cookie sheet or pizza pan. Edges may be trimmed easily (like heart shapes, etc.). Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes; cool. Cut into any shape you like. Decorate with icing, just like a birthday cake. Good plain also.

title: zuppa di cozze(mussel soup)
directions: Scrub and wash the mussels.
Place in a large covered stockpot over moderate heat, just until they open.
Discard any that do not open.
Strain mussel liquid.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick soft oleo with graham crackers and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks oleo and powdered sugar no less than 15 minutes with an electric beater.
Spread over cracker crust and cover with sliced bananas.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cut up cherries.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water.
Add cold water; cool.
Add pineapple juice and ice cream; blend.
Add ginger ale and serve immediately.
Makes 40 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: Melt margarine in electric skillet at 250°.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add catsup, barbecue sauce and sugar; stir until bubbly.
Add chicken that has been salted.
Pour Coca-Cola over chicken.
Reduce heat to simmer (175°).
Cook for 1 hour.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and spread on a large tray or plate.
Mix the chili sauce and cocktail sauce.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Top with the shrimp.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add milk, then flour mixture gradually, until blended.
Refrigerate dough until easy to handle.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface (roll thin for crisp cookies, thick for softer cookies).
Cut with floured cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush cookies with milk or egg white; sprinkle with toppings.
Bake for approximately 12 minutes.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Fry bacon and crumble into drained beef and onion.
Add beans, catsup, vinegar and mustard. Put in crock-pot and cook 4 to 5 hours on low heat.
Easy and delicious.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread kraut in bottom of a 2-quart oblong dish.
Add next 4 in layers, dotting tomatoes with dressing.
Mix crushed crackers, seed and butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on High or bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers, sugar, cinnamon and melted margarine.	Pack
firmly into a greased 9-inch pan.
Reserve a few crumbs for topping,

title: great grandma's carrot cake
directions: In a middle sized saucepan put the first 8 ingredients.
Simmer these ingredients together for 5minutes.
Then cover and let set for 12 hours (no less).
Then add walnuts, flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Bake in 2 oiled loaf pans or 1 tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. (Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around the edges of the pan.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in last 4 ingredients.
Stir hard until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Good served on party rye bread.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Pour about 1 1/2 quarts of milk and 1 cup of sugar in a double boiler and let it get warm.
Add 1 large tablespoon of cornstarch and 1 large tablespoon of flour (shake it well in a mixer); add to milk.
Pour in slowly the beaten eggs (whites and yellow) in a 4-quart freezer (or 6 for a 6-quart freezer).
Cook over a double boiler until it becomes a custard.
Pour into freezer and add 2 cups of sugar (3 cups for a 6-quart freezer).
Add vanilla.
Also add fruit (crushed pineapple) or chocolate syrup, whatever you want or other things.
Add Pet milk and finish filling can with milk. Let it cool before starting freezer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt; add to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Add nuts and mix. Pour into two loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: caramel glazed - hot milk cake
directions: Combine milk and margarine in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat until margarine melts, stirring occasionally.
Cool to 120°.
Combine sugar and eggs in large bowl; beat at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Sift flour mixture over egg mixture, beating at low speed.
Gradually add milk mixture to egg mixture, beating at high speed.
Spoon batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is golden brown. Immediately spread Caramel Glaze over warm cake.
Yield:
16 servings.
Contains 141 calories per serving.

title: georgia peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread peaches evenly in bottom of pan.
Stir together Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Batter will be lumpy and consistency of pancake batter.
Pour batter evenly over peaches.
Lightly sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until top is lightly browned.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form batter.
Drop by tablespoons in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown and drain.

title: easy peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
In large mixer bowl; beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add bisquick and vanilla, mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Press candy kiss in center of each cookie immediately after baking.

title: artichokes with flair
directions: Quarter drained artichoke hearts and spread over bottom of an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Spoon spinach over artichokes.
Melt butter and cream cheese in a small saucepan (cream cheese will be lumpy). Pour and spread over spinach.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle well with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: roquefort dressing(from overrock inn)
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Do not overstir.

title: chuck roast bake
directions: Place roast in center of heavy foil in roasting pan.
Spread roast with steak sauce.
Sprinkle onion soup over the top.
Spread mushroom soup over all.
Seal the foil at sides and top. Completely enclose the meat but leave an air space above meat. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Makes its own gravy.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Put oil in a pan.
Finely slice onion and fry in oil until golden brown.
Add paprika.
Stir it around and add meat.
Add green pepper, celery, chopped tomato, bay leaf and cloves.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Steam the meat until it draws juice, then sprinkle flour on meat.
Add water and simmer until tender (about 2 hours).
Add potatoes for the last 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice, noodles or bread dumplings.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Include orange rind when making pastry dough.
I use Pillsbury pie crusts and grate orange rind over crust.
Mix rhubarb, strawberries, sugar, orange juice, tapioca, nutmeg and salt together in large bowl.
Turn into prepared pie shell.
Dot the filling with butter.
Cover with remaining pie crust; moisten, seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in crust in several places.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes or until top crust is lightly browned.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: punch for 100
directions: Boil water and dissolve sugar.
Add
all
other liquids and mix.
Use any food coloring you like.
Put
in
open
containers and freeze; use big pickle jars or
candy jars.
Leave headspace in jars.
Will freeze in about 12 hours.
Set out to thaw.
Do not add ice, just stir.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and brown chopped onion.
Add rice, bouillon cubes and water.
Mix well and bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff (low-fat)
directions: Slice beef into bite-size pieces.
Fry pieces with garlic in a nonstick skillet or pan coated with nonstick vegetable oil spray. Just before beef is done, add mushrooms.
While meat cooks, prepare sauce.

title: creamed peas and deviled ham
directions: Add enough milk to soup to make 2 cups.
Blend in ham.
Fold in drained peas.
Stir lightly and heat.
Serve over toast, waffles or baked potatoes.

title: yam casserole
directions: Pour yams into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle topping over yams.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter with hands; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls and place on wax paper.

title: mel's chili
directions: Saute onion in pan.
Add hamburger.
Cook until hamburger is well done.
Add all the ingredients above.
Add options, if desired.

title: pennsylvania dutch shoo-fly pie
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter. In a separate bowl, mix molasses, baking soda and water.
Stir in salt, egg and two cups of flour-butter mixture.
Pour into prepared pie shells and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute onion slowly in margarine.
Combine muffin mix, egg, milk and corn.
Place in greased 8-inch square pan.
Add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cup cheese to onion.
Spread over batter. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: eat it all cake
directions: Bake cake mix, cool.
Mix pudding, let cool.
Put pineapple on cake first, then pudding, sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Top with coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mixing well, then salad oil; mix thoroughly. Add oats, cornflakes, coconut, nuts and vanilla; stirring to combine.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. form into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake for 12 minutes. Allow to cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Heat and stir in saucepan until thick the first 4 ingredients. Take from stove.
Add catsup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of soda crackers.
Sprinkle this cup on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: In top of double boiler, cook sugar, butter and eggs for 10 minutes until custard.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Add graham crackers and marshmallows to cooled mixture.
Press in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Ice.
Can put in refrigerator overnight if desired.

title: low salt seasoning
directions: *Or omit entirely if on a limited sodium intake.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients. Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: italian spinach and shells
directions: Boil shells; do not overcook.
Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Mix cheeses, egg and season. Add spinach; stir well.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Place in greased dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over. Sprinkle little cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne quickie
directions: Brown beef, add onions, garlic and oregano.
Cook until beef is brown and onions are tender.
Add soup, water and vinegar. Simmer 30 minutes, stir now and then.

title: sweet 'n sour hot dogs
directions: Heat jelly and cocktail sauce together until well blended. Pour over hot dogs that have been cut into lengths of about 1 to 2 inches.
Bake in oven at 350° until hot dogs are heated and flavors blended.
Sauce can be saved and used with more hot dogs.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain and stir in salt and pepper.
Spread beef in pie plate.
Cover with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife comes out clean from the center (about 30 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes.
(If using a 9-inch pie plate, decrease milk to 1 cup, Bisquick to 1/2 cup and eggs to 2.)

title: everyday turkey burgers lo-fat!
directions: Mix all together and shape into patties.
Pan-fry (with vegetable spray) or grill, like normal hamburgers.

title: coke pork chops
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
In single layer, place 4 to 6 pork chops, 1-inch to 1 1/2-inches thick.
Top each chop with sliced onion and barbecue sauce.
Pour enough Coke around chops to come halfway up around.
Seal foil; bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix well together.
Knead as for bread.
Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Roll into bread sticks and brush with 1 beaten egg, mixed with a little water.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush the garlic powder, salt and oil (mixed together) on bread sticks while warm.
Can add more garlic powder, if you wish.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on edged cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker pie
directions: Combine the pecans, coconut, 1/2 cup of sugar and cracker crumbs in first bowl.
Beat egg whites stiffly; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in first mixture.
Pour in buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: harrisons coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Mix well.
Add hot water and beat well.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan. Top batter with more brown sugar and cinnamon nuts if you want to.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients.
Add flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Mix well and refrigerate 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: susan's texas hash
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in bacon grease until nearly tender.
Add ground beef and finish browning.
Drain meat and combine in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish with the Ro-Tel tomatoes, noodles (uncooked), salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in half cup of hot water.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour and salt together.
Mix eggs, milk and shortening; add gradually to flour.
Beat until smooth with egg whisk or mixer.
Should take about 1 minute.
Pour into greased popover tins, Pyrex cups or muffin pans to 1/3 full. Bake 20 minutes at temperature given.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 15 minutes until popovers are firm.
Yield:
about 8 large popovers.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Combine chicken with paprika, garlic and black pepper. Combine 3/4 cup broth, cornstarch and soy sauce. Set aside. Stir-fry chicken in a tablespoon hot oil. Cook 1 minute or more. Add onion, celery, green peppers and 1/2 cup broth.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 minutes. Add tomato sauce. Add broth, cornstarch and soy sauce mixture. Cook until sauce thickens (1 minute). Serve over rice.

title: marinade
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Pour over meat and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: microwave minestrone
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine the carrots, celery, zucchini, yellow pepper and onion. Drizzle with oil. Toss to coat. Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on High for 15 minutes. Yield: 5 servings.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box, but do not let stand.
Spoon stuffing into a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of mix, overlapping if necessary.
Combine soup, milk and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add garlic powder, onions and salt to taste.
Smear on ham slices and roll.
Close with toothpick. Freeze.
After frozen, allow to thaw at room temperature for 15 minutes and slice into bite size.
Ready to serve within 30 minutes.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook rice by package directions.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix in tuna, dressing and peas until well mixed. Top with saltines; spread with just enough margarine to coat them. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until crackers are just browned.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place half of potatoes in baking dish with chopped onion and half of shredded cheese, half of chopped ham and salt (if desired). Add rest of potatoes, chopped onion, ham and cheese on top. Mix soup and milk and pour over all. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls onto bottom of 13-inch oblong pan (spray with Pam).
Add sausage and sprinkle oregano, Italian seasoning and garlic powder over sausage.
Layer potatoes, cheese, egg and milk mixture and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef round-up
directions: Pound steak very thin. Combine the salt, pepper, paprika
and garlic and rub both sides of steak very well.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with a fork or pastry cutter until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13 pan and bake 20 minutes at 325 F.
Let cool.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream yolks with sugar.
Add vanilla, cream and milk.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to boiling point.
Boil slightly.
Beat 12 whites with enough sugar to hold together. When milk mixture is finished, sprinkle with nutmeg. Fold egg whites into milk.
Serve.
Add spirits if desired. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: First Layer:
Blend flour and oleo; add nuts and press in 8 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Combine.
Stir apricot mixture into sausage mixture.
Heat to thicken.
Add 2 cups drained pineapple tidbits.
Serve over rice.

title: hello dolly dream bars
directions: Melt oleo
in
pan (about 6 x 9-inch size).
Add crumbs evenly,
then
condensed
milk.
Sprinkle morsels over mixture and pecans
on	top.
Place
in
350° oven and immediately cut back to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn off and leave in oven 10 minutes longer.
Cut in squares or strips.

title: two-hour bread("nevertheless, wheat for man...."  d&c 89:17)
directions: Step I:
Measure oil, honey and salt into large mixing bowl. (Add 1 cup powdered milk or 1 egg for extra nourishment.)
Add 3 cups warm water.
Add yeast to 1 cup warm water and let stand while you add 5 cups flour and stir in well for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: pineapple cucumber lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 3 graham cracker crusts.
Chill at least an hour.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Clean berries.
Crush so that all are reduced to a pulp. Measure 4 1/2 cups.
Add water if necessary.
Mix Sure-Jell with berries into large saucepan.
Place over high heat.
Stir until comes to a hard boil.
Add sugar at once.
Bring to a full, rolling boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Quickly ladle into clean, hot jars.
Cover with 1/8 inch of paraffin.
Cool slowly.

title: pretty pink salad
directions: Combine gelatin with 3/4 cup hot water.
Add softened cream cheese to remaining 1/4 cup hot water.
Stir until mixed well.
Add to gelatin and stir until well mixed.
Drain pineapple; measure juice and add enough water to it to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add drained pineapple to gelatin and then add cup of liquid.
Drain orange segments; add to gelatin.
Stir in marshmallows last.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: gratin of asparagus
directions: Discard tough end of asparagus.
Cut off tips about 2 1/2 inches from tip ends and slice remainder of spear into 1/2 inch pieces.
Bring a large saucepan of lightly salted water to a boil, add asparagus tips and pieces and boil for 2 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove asparagus and plunge it into a bowl of cold water to stop cooking.
Drain well.
Place cream and garlic in a small saucepan and simmer over low heat until cream is slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salt water 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Season layers of potato with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with onions and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 10 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust; crimp edges.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand loosely for 8 to 10 hours.
Refrigerate for 4 days.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Add vanilla; then applesauce.
Be sure it is blended well.
Pour into pan.
Before baking, sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over the top of the batter.
Then, sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1 cup chopped nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in mixture and add oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy, add 1/4 cup sugar and beat to stiff peaks . Pour batter over egg whites and blend.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: night before french toast casserole
directions: Use extra butter to grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange bread in single layer in pan.
In a bowl, beat together all ingredients except butter.
Pour over bread.
Dot bread with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo together.
Stir in pecans.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Do not beat. Add to chocolate mixture.
Fill cupcake pans 3/4 full and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix butter, eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Next add flour, mini chocolate chips and nuts.
After mixing well pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nutty noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain.
Add cooked noodles with other ingredients, except chow mein noodles and nuts.
Mix ingredients well; salt to taste.
Place in a large casserole dish and cover.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and nuts.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: basic bavarian
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon into dessert glasses.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and fresh or canned fruit, as desired.

title: mama's barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters(for 25 people)
directions: Drain oysters, saving liquid.
Remove any bits and shells. Mix crumbs, butter and seasonings.
Spread 1/3 over bottom of one greased baking pan.
Cover with half of oysters.
Mix milk or cream and oyster liquid and pour over top of oysters.
Cover with remaining crumbs; bake.
One cup finely chopped, partially cooked celery may be added.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over coconut and nut crust.
Mix and drop on top of cake using a teaspoon the cream cheese, sugar and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marinated crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except crabmeat in a stainless steel or porcelain bowl. Mix thoroughly, then add crabmeat. Toss gently with a fork until mixed well and moistened. Cover with plastic and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight. Serve well chilled. Serves 4. Will last up to 5 days in refrigerator.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and stir until well blended.
Mix together remaining ingredients and let stand for 24 hours before serving, mixing occasionally.
Add onion slices before serving (optional).

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up hen.
Place in pan and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in butter.
Simmer until tender.
Remove hen.
Cut into small pieces as desired.
Reserve stock.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: All all together and simmer about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
This may be brought to a boil on stove and cooked in the oven on 250°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
In saucepan, mix butter, flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Melt and spread in medium to large pizza pan.
Bake in 375° oven until golden.
Remove, cool completely.
Add next layer.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into pieces and moisten with milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into cakes and fry quickly until brown.

title: stella's roasted chicken
directions: Skin and quarter chickens.
Place in roaster seasoned with Tony's and garlic powder with sliced onion on top in wine 1-inch deep.
Roast at 350°.
After 30 minutes, add Worcestershire, mushrooms, potatoes and carrots.
Continue cooking for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups cereal and boiling water in medium bowl; blend well.
Cool.
Add buttermilk, oil and egg well.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in medium bowl; stir in cereal mixture, mini chips and apricots, just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: black-eyed pea fritters
directions: Cover peas well with water and soak for 30 minutes.
Drain and place on chopping board, a few at a time.
Roll, using rolling pin with enough pressure to split peas in half.
Return all peas to large bowl and cover all well with water, allowing hulls to float to top of water.
Pour off water and hulls; continue rinsing until all hulls are removed.
Cover again with warm water and soak 1 hour.
Drain and blend, using 1/3 of peas with 1/2 cup of water each time.
Transfer mixture to a large bowl after each blending. Add seasonings, onion and peppers; mix.
Using a teaspoon to drop fritter into hot oiled skillet, brown lightly on each side.
Serve hot.

title: chalupas
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Add just enough water to cover beans.
Cook very slowly all day.
One to 2 hours before serving, remove meat and shred; return to pot.
Serve over chips (tortilla) with lettuce, tomatoes, green onion, cheese and sour cream.

title: fresh berries and cream(rote grutze)
directions: Put apricots and cherries in saucepan and add enough water to cover.
Stew the fruits slowly.
When the apricots and cherries are almost done, add the strawberries.
Do not overcook.
Add sugar slowly and taste for desired sweetness.
Add the raspberries and bring to a boil.
Remove from stove; add the gelatin.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours or more.
Serve with heavy cream or vanilla sauce.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Blend together brown sugar, white sugar, shortening, eggs and self-rising flour.
Add the other ingredients: coconut, oatmeal, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fluffy mushroom-rice saute
directions: In a large skillet cook bacon.
Remove to paper towel.
Cool. Drain all but 2 tablespoons of the drippings.
Add rice, onion and mushrooms.
Saute until rice is browned.
Add water and salt and bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Crumble bacon and toss with rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mac sausage and broccoli bake
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add all remaining ingredients to the macaroni and cheese dinner and mix well. Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: rotini bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper, seasoning and 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well and place into baking dish.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth. If sugar doesn't seem to want to dissolve, place small bowl in larger bowl of hot water and continue mixing. Makes 14 ounces.

title: spinach pita
directions: Wash Spinach:
Fill sink with water and empty spinach bags into sink.
Lay a towel on the counter.
Swish the spinach around to remove any remaining sand/bugs/grass (I have found all three in various combinations).
Remove any large stems and place leaves on towel to drain and dry.
Time consuming.
Air dry 2 to 3 hours or pat dry with another towel if time is a limiting factor.
(Usually it has to set there while you chop the cheese and onions anyway.)

title: country soup(sopa de espinaca; potaje)
directions: Saute garlic, onion and pepper in olive oil. Add garbanzo beans with water, bouillon, potatoes, tomatoes or spaghetti sauce, parsley and saffron. Simmer covered until potatoes are soft. Add spinach, mix and cover, simmer at least a few minutes.

title: cinnamon-walnut coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
