title: hard cinnamon candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until hard crack stage.
Add cinnamon oil and red food coloring.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet; after it sets up, break into bite size pieces.

title: nevelle's yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve the package of yeast in warm water.
Add cooking oil, sugar, buttermilk and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into bread tray and work into stiff dough.
Make out biscuits, but do not pat down flat.
Let set 1 hour and bake until golden brown at 400° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Blend in soda, cinnamon, ground cloves and salt, then add flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoon into balls; roll in sugar.
Place balls 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding from box with the pineapple and juice.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix and chill.

title: sand art brownies
directions: Layer the first 7 ingredients in order in a quart mason jar. Then attach a note to add: 3 eggs, 2/3 cup oil and 1 tsp. vanilla. Mix and pour into a greased 9 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 32 minutes.

title: pecan logs
directions: Beat milk, sugar and flavoring until smooth.
Knead and shape into logs (4), each about 5 inches long.
Place on waxed paper. Melt caramels, butter and water in top of double boiler.
Pour onto logs, a little at a time.
Roll in nuts.

title: cheese ring
directions: Spray Jell-O ring mold with nonstick spray.
Mix all of the ingredients, except the strawberries.
Press mixture into mold. Refrigerate for 6 hours or preferably overnight.
Empty onto plate.
Put preserves in center.

title: marinara pasta sauce
directions: Place the sliced garlic, chopped parsley and onion in a microwave-safe dish. Add oil.
Microwave on High power for 1 minute.
Slightly break up the tomatoes. Add to onion-garlic mixture.
Microwave on High power for about 8 minutes, stirring at least once.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Let stand for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once. Add fresh basil leaves.
Serve sauce hot or cold over pasta or rice. Also good served with meat loaf, meatballs or pork chops. Serves 4.

title: greek eggplant soup
directions: In a 5-quart pot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until the onions are translucent.
Add the herbs and spices and saute on low for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the crushed tomatoes with juice, eggplant, garbanzo beans, water and fructose.
Heat the mixture on high until it comes to a boil.
Then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add the spinach and Romano cheese and simmer for 15 more minutes.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Mix all items together.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Let cool for 15 or 20 minutes.
Mix strawberries in and pour into baked pie shell.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter apples or slice as desired.
Put 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon to taste on each quarter or slice.
Wrap biscuit around each.
(Put 1 teaspoon oleo along with sugar and cinnamon.)
Boil 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar.
Pour over apples-biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Great with vanilla ice cream or plain.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Stir until blended.
Cool.
Add eggs stirring until blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and stir into mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts stirring until blended. Spread in well greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until slight imprint remains when touched with finger. Don't overbake.
Cut into bars or squares while still warm.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Keep in refrigerator.
Drink 1/2 cup or 2 ounces daily.
Good for everything.

title: maureen's french toast
directions: Cook sugar, butter and syrup until syrupy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread apple slices, raisins and nuts over this.
Slice bread and place on top.
Whisk together remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let stand at room temperature overnight; mix thoroughly. Shape into balls and roll in finely chopped dried beef.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt fat in 4-quart pot, using medium heat.
Add ground beef and stir frequently to break up lumps of meat.
Add seasonings and blend.
Add vegetables and water.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni buffet skillet
directions: Dice onion and garlic; saute with ground beef.
Add uncooked macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir in cheese sauce packet.
Cover tightly.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Fold in remaining ingredients all at once.
Place 1/2 of mixture into long Pyrex dish.
Let set about 1 hour.
Spread on sour cream.
Pour on remaining mixture and let set.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Stuff chilies with Jack cheese (don't worry if chilies tear or come apart).
Arrange side by side in prepared dish.
Beat eggs in medium size bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Fold pancake batter into eggs and pour over chilies.
Sprinkle Cheddar over top.
Bake 30 minutes or until puffed, firm and lightly browned around edges.
Serve immediately.
Spoon salsa on top. Makes 6 servings.
Per serving:
541 calories and 33 g. fat.

title: coconut balls
directions: Melt butter and pour over nuts. In a large bowl, mix coconut, sugar, milk and vanilla. Add butter and nuts and mix well. Shape into balls and chill for about 3 hours.

title: eskimo balls
directions: Stir all together.
Chill in fridge.
You can roll into balls and coat with confectioners sugar to make Eskimo balls, or eat it with a spoon as fast as you can!

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Press rolls in bottom of pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Add grated cheese.
Mix milk, eggs and oregano.
Pour over cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: red cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel, core and spear cucumbers.
Soak in water and lime for 24 hours.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Melt Hershey bars over hot water and add Hershey syrup; add to sugar-egg mixture.
Add baking soda to buttermilk and fold into sugar-egg mixture alternately with flour and salt.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in greased tube pan 325 degrees for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Poke holes into warm cake with handle of small wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, pour caramel sauce over cake.
Cool. Spread cool whip over the top of cake and sprinkle with chopped snickers.
Refrigerate until served.

title: pumpkin pie(9-inch)
directions: Put everything into a blender; mix together until smooth. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
May sprinkle cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger on top or add to mixture before pouring into shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add flour and stir until smooth (1 minute).
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil and remove from heat.
Makes 2 cups.

title: microwave fried rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish; microwave on High for 40 seconds.
Add eggs; cover.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir; re-cover and microwave for an additional minute.
Add remaining ingredients; stir gently to blend and microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until firm-tender, not completely cooked.
Cool 6 hours or overnight.
Peel potatoes; coarsely grate.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for one hour (covered for 1/2 hour and uncovered for last 1/2 hour).

title: beer bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Then pour 1/4 cup melted butter on top and bake another 25 minutes.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Melt chips and wax together.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Pour on wax paper to dry.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: In an 8 X 10 pan layer sliced peaches in bottom and cover with juice.
Sprinkle cinnamon over peaches and a little sugar if tart.
Cover with a dry yellow cake mix.
Slice 1 cube butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Prepare whipped topping according to package directions. Blend in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Break cake into bite size pieces and place 1/2 in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 1/3 of cheese mixture.
Repeat with remaining cake and cover with the remaining cheese mixture.
Spoon pie filling on top; chill to set.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: *Use 1 package for small casserole.
Use 2 packages for a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and flour. Add sugar, milk and butter. Boil until thick. Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: miss reba's simple brownies
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Pour in greased 9x13 in. baking dish and bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix and beat first 4 ingredients, then mix dry ingredients. Add the soda water to the wet mixture.
Gradually add the dry mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 or 45 minutes or until done.

title: fresh pear cake(makes one 10-inch tube cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch fluted tube or tube pan.
Combine pears, granulated sugar and nuts; mix lightly. Let stand 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Blend in oil and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in pear mixture.
Pour into prepared pan, spreading evenly to edges.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove to rack to cool completely.
Dust lightly with powdered sugar just before serving, if desired.

title: cabbage roll soup
directions: Since
I
don't measure you just sort of have to figure your meat, cabbage, rice ratio on your own.

title: pecan pie(servings:  8)
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and corn syrup.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell and top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except pecans, and pour into a pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and liqueur.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add chips.
Drop by spoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto baking sheets.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheet to cool 2 minutes after removing.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Season with savor salt and lemon pepper.
Mix to taste with buttermilk Ranch dressing or Italian dressing or a 1/2 and 1/2 combination.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: tandy kake
directions: Grease a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients, except peanut butter and chocolate, together.
Pour into cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute. Melt peanut butter (microwave or double boiler).
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate until hard.
Melt chocolate.
Spread on top of peanut butter.
Refrigerate again.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in a 3-quart glass casserole dish. Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper over potatoes.
Toss to coat evenly.
Dot with butter and pour milk over top.
Cover and microwave 20 to 24 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir once during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil and water. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sour cream, grated chocolate, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut. Turn batter into a well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix in a large bowl the chocolate bars, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer celery, onions and broccoli in enough chicken broth to cover the vegetables and simmer until soft.
Add the salt, pepper, nutmeg and milk.
Heat until almost boiling, but do not boil. Thicken with a cornstarch mixture (starch and water).
Add the cheeses.
Stir and remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir again to blend in cheese.

title: spatini dip
directions: Mix well sour cream and Spatini spaghetti sauce mix.
This is very good with raw vegetables.

title: banana split cake pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and confectioners sugar and spread in bottom of graham cracker crust.
Spread pineapple on top of cream cheese.
Place sliced bananas on top of pineapple.
Frost with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries on top.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Then mix the ingredients and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook until all ingredients are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Add 1 can of broth where chicken was cooked.
Take cooked chicken and bone it into bite size pieces.
Set aside.

title: old time beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, thoroughly brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot shortening, turning often.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, to keep from sticking.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked bulgur-mushroom pilaf
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Put the broth/water mixture into a saucepan and heat until very hot.
In a 2-quart baking dish, heat the margarine and oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and shallots; saute 1 minute.
Add the mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in bulgur, thyme, pepper and hot broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and put into the preheated oven.
Cook 25 minutes.
Stir in the parsley and nuts if using (optional 1 teaspoon toasted pine nuts or almonds finely chopped).

title: hot cider
directions: Mix all together. Store in jar with lid.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water or can be put in a large electric coffeepot for self serve. Add water to taste.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons flour and sugar with cherries in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening and add milk to make a soft dough.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board to fit utensil and score in 6 squares.
Place over cherries.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: apple pie
directions: Dice apples to cover bottom of dish (5 to 6).
Trim crust off light bread and trim bread into 3 slices to cover apples.
Mix ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli tidbits
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into bite size balls.
Place on greased baking sheets and heat at 325° for 15 minutes or until brown.
May be prepared ahead.
May be frozen before cooking. Serves 20.

title: ramen noodle coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onions and
sesame seeds.
Mix together in another bowl, oil, vinegar sugar and flavor packet.
Toss together.
When ready to serve, add almonds and uncooked Ramen noodles.
Chunks of cooked chicken could be added.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole; boil chicken breasts and break into bite size pieces; put on top of broccoli.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix together crackers, sugar, and butter.
Press half of mixture into bottom of pan.
In separate bowl, combine milk, Cool Whip and lemonade.
Spread over cracker mixture.
Top with remaining crackers.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: cheerios caramel nut crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter the jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.
Spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool until slightly firm, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Loosen with metal spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Store in a covered container.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: With a fork, cream the cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1 cup pecans.
Mix well by hand.
Let the mixture harden in the refrigerator for about 45 minutes.
Remove and shape into a ball.
Roll in reserved pecans.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix the corn, flour, sugar, egg, butter and milk in medium bowl. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and top with crackers. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: favorite chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup, sour cream and mushrooms in casserole dish. Layer on top cracker crumbs, cheese, cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: morning rice(breakfast)
directions: Boil rice in 1 cup of unsalted water; remove from heat.
Stir in rest.
Cover and let stand.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce on bottom of clear glass bowl. Add the other vegetable in layers. Do not toss! Spread mayonnaise evenly over the top. Sprinkle with sugar and layer the cheddar cheese on top. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Sprinkle bacon over the salad before serving. Makes 10-12 servings.

title: hershey's syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, then put in Hershey's syrup, vanilla and nuts. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sherry's brownies
directions: Remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces chocolate chips and beat until thickened.
Spread over cooled brownies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In casserole dish, lay a layer of sliced potatoes in bottom of dish; add layer of carrots, cabbage, peppers and onions and repeat layers.
Pat ground beef (uncooked) on top of layers and add stewed tomatoes on top of ground beef.
Sprinkle lemon pepper on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips.
Mix very well.
Add the chocolate chips, stirring them in.
Pour batter into a large Bundt pan, which has been greased and floured lightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes, depending on the oven.
Let stand on wire rack for a few minutes. Remove cake from pan and cool on rack until completely cool. Either ice it with a chocolate icing or sprinkle powdered sugar over the top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; chill in refrigerator.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased baking sheet.
Cook 10 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients together over medium heat about 15 minutes. Pour back into ketchup bottle. May be kept indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: hollendacke ragge brood(holland rye bread)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 3 cups boiling water.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in 250° oven 2 1/2 hours, longer if needed. Cover with a pan of the same size.
Put cup of water in oven while baking.

title: uncooked bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel and cut up the onions.
Cut up the cucumbers.
Fill a gallon jar with sliced onions and cukes.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over all.
Let set 5 days.
Shake up every day.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic salt, then add enchilada sauce, cream of mushroom soup, green chilies and water; let simmer.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of tortillas, meat mixture and cheese; repeat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, 30 minutes, covered and 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve.

title: caramel delight
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and nuts. Stir in melted butter. Spread in a thin layer on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown. Cool and crumble.
Put half of these crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spoon caramel topping over crumbs. Slice softened ice cream over topping. Top with remaining crumbs. Freeze until firm. Cut in squares to serve.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt butter.
Mix salts and sauces in butter.
Pour sauce in bottom of baking pan; mix with remaining mixture.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat the egg and 1/2 cup milk.
Cut in lard into flour mixture.
Add milk and egg mixture. Roll out and cut in small squares.
Drop into boiling broth.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruit.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juice concentrate, stir until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in whipped topping, fold in fruit.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and slice.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: alex kalberer's vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake as a crust at recommended temperature and time.
Blend the cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed, Lawry's salt and chopped onion together.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust and top with vegetables.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese out of refrigerator to soften to room temperature.
Once softened, cream together.
Make into a ball and put into refrigerator.
Should set overnight for best results. Serve next day.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Spray pan.
Line pan with biscuits; sprinkle with grated cheese.
(I find Cheddar works best.)
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken devine
directions: Boil chicken breasts in the following:
salt, peppercorns, bay leaf, water, celery tops, rosemary and parsley flakes.
Arrange chicken on asparagus.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour this mixture over the chicken breasts.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top, then cover with grated sharp cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: one dish supper
directions: Brown meat in small amount of fat.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add vegetables, soup and spices.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, depending on the thickness of the meat.

title: strawberry-topped cheesecake(dieter's recipe)
directions: Preparation Time: 20 minutes.
Cooking Time: 40 minutes. Chilling Time: Several hours.
(Contains 206 calories.)

title: gazpacho
directions: Cut first 4 ingredients in small pieces.
Put everything in blender and blend for 1/2 minute.
Serve cold with croutons and chives.

title: apple strudel
directions: *If using canned apples, don't use the apple pie fillings. Comstock's pie sliced apples are recommended and fill 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.

title: rum or whiskey cake
directions: Beat cake according to box instructions and add all ingredients except nuts.
Fold nuts in at end.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Make glaze.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap bacon tightly around chicken.
Place chipped beef on bottom of glass pan.
Place chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread on top.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered. Can easily be reheated or frozen.
Serves 8.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Boil peas for 2 minutes; drain, let cool.
Wash and separate cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Add onions and celery. Sprinkle dressing mix over mixture and add mayonnaise.
Stir.
When peas are cool, add them to mixture and stir carefully.
Serve cold.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce and mix with sour cream; spread on bottom of oblong baking dish.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add seasoning, water and taco sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over lettuce. Layer tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wrap slices of dried beef around chicken breasts.
Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine sour cream, soup, water and raw rice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well and pour
into
unbaked
pie
shell
(9-inch). Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
If desired, add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon allspice.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Pat it out in pie pan.

title: hot pickled cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water about 10 minutes. Drain.
While cauliflower cooks, combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan. Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked cauliflower.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Put 6 slices of bread in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of the crumbled bacon and cheeses.
Top with remaining 6 slices of bread.
Add remaining bacon and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over bacon and cheeses.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream the butter, eggs, honey and sugar.
Add milk and stir well.
Add rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 375°.

title: picnic chick
directions: Put melted butter in small bowl. Put parsley, bread crumbs, onion flakes and Parmesan cheese on wax paper.
Dip drumsticks in butter then in other ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix everything and pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Can use cream cheese icing or a glaze of powdered sugar and milk.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins in water until it evaporates.
Cool.
Cream shortening and eggs till fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with raisins and vanilla.
Mix well, shape dough into small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bade at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: bake beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until pink is out. Drain and mix other ingredients. Add to hamburger mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare and dice potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Gently boil potatoes 10 minutes in 1 cup boiling water.
Add salt.
Chop onion and parsley.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Fold crushed crackers and pecans into beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. After cool, top with whipped cream.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, including juice.
Let congeal completely.

title: minute chicken
directions: Chop chicken in serving pieces.
Combine all ingredients and marinate chicken.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Sprinkle chopped onion over chicken and serve.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Sift together flour, soda, cocoa and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla.
Add boiling water; stir only until well blended.
Divide between 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool completely before frosting with Chocolate Frosting.

title: pork chops quick and easy
directions: Slice mushrooms, celery and onions. Season pork and brown in oil; remove pork from pan and add vegetables. Stir-fry until wilted. Add soup, water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil; add rice. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Lay pork chops on top of rice mixture. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until rice is done.

title: applesauce and peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: tennessee nut balls
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and roll into little balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bottom of cookie is light brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook popcorn; set aside in very large foil roaster pan.
Bring ingredients to a gentle boil in a large saucepan.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Keep stirring until foamy. Pour syrup over popcorn, coating evenly.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, tossing every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread out on wax paper and separate as it cools.
Store in airtight containers. Makes lots!
Good for gifts at Christmas.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix other ingredients and bake for 1 hour in medium oven.
Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch plastic or glass pan:
lettuce, onion, green pepper, celery, eggs and bacon (both eggs and bacon should be broken into pieces).
Mix Hellmann's mayonnaise and sugar. Frost over salad and sprinkle with cheese.
Let set for 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: spanish omelette
directions: Saute potato in 1/4 cup oil until lightly browned and tender. Remove and leave a little oil to saute the onion.
Beat eggs with the baking powder and add salt and pepper.

title: popover pizza
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned (I add green pepper with ground chuck and onion).
Stir to crumble meat; drain.
Add sauce mix, tomato sauce and water, mixing well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: hamburger gravy("lumpy stew")
directions: Our relatives make this all the time and they and their friends tell me it is great!

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup and salt until soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add butter.
Pour over corn.
Grease fingertips and palms; press into balls.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Quarter each biscuit and roll in sugar mixture.
Place in Bundt pan.
Mix the brown sugar and melted butter.
Pour over coated biscuits.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Dump on plate and ready to eat.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs, oil, water, pumpkin, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Beat until smooth. Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
May add nuts, if desired. Yields 24 servings.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: *Soak candy overnight in 1/2 cup whiskey.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Dice and boil potatoes, then chill.
Boil eggs, then chill. Cut up egg whites.
Chop celery, onion and pickles.
Mix with cool diced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: delicious chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour together; mix well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk to egg yolks.
Beat.
Add to dry mixture.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla and oleo.
Stir.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 big or 2 small pies.
Double for 2 good pies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla and mix.
Add all dry ingredients; add zucchini and mix. Add the raisins, coconut and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pans for one hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Mix
butter, white sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter until creamy.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a
time.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder mixture alternately with milk, starting and ending with
flour.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake
1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Gas oven 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no name salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until jello sets up.
Serve on leaf of lettuce.

title: fruit salad
directions: You can add grapes, cherries, coconut (optional) or pecans (optional).

title: puffed apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In blender, put eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, yogurt, salt and cinnamon.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan in oven.
Add apple slices to baking dish.
Return to oven until butter sizzles.
Do not burn.
Pour batter over apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: outdoor salad
directions: Cut lettuce, tomatoes, radishes, green onions, white onion, cucumbers and pickles in large bowl.
Toss to mix.
Serve with your choice of dressing.
We prefer Ranch to bring out the flavor. Great for outdoor cooking.

title: chicken pie
directions: Make a roux of margarine and flour; when bubbling, add chicken broth and milk.
Stir with a wire whisk to blend.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and smooth.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
You may want to add celery salt and onion powder to taste.
Mixture will thicken a little as the crust bakes.
You will want the mixture to be about as thick as cream of chicken soup, half diluted.
If you need more broth, add cream of chicken, mushroom or celery soup and dilute to desired thickness and mix with the thickened broth.
Well drained peas or canned mixed vegetables may be added to broth.
Place chicken in a baking dish; pour thickened broth over chicken.

title: company chicken cutlets
directions: Dip cutlets in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Brown in oil and set aside.
Saute garlic and mushrooms in butter.
Add wine, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Heat thoroughly cream of mushroom soup and 1 soup can of milk until smooth.
Set aside.

title: oven stew
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy casserole or Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours, at 300° for 4 hours or 350° for 3 hours.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, carrots, egg yolks and lemon juice.
In separate bowl mix flour and baking powder then combine with carrot mixture.
Combine baking soda and warm water then add to remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in ring mold at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted butter, add beaten eggs and pecans to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 35 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Butter casserole dish; add a thin layer of Doritos and chicken.
Repeat Doritos and chicken.
Heat chicken broth and flour to thicken.
Stir in mushroom soup and part of cheese to this and melt.
Add green chilies and onion, thicken.
Pour over chicken and Doritos.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put together as you would a potato salad.
Diet mayo makes this a dream.
Serve over crisp lettuce.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Pour in a greased oblong pan.
Poke holes in cake after done.
Heat pineapple and sugar, then pour over hot cake.
Mix pudding as directed and spoon over pineapple mixture.
Slice bananas and place over pudding. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Place sliced cherries on top.
Cut in squares and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: * Parboil or steam vegetables slightly.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Fold crab meat into mixture.
Pour mixture into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with a variety of crackers.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Pour into pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken poupon
directions: In large bowl or plastic bag, put all seasonings. Add chicken. Mix to coat. Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: grandma's custard
directions: Cook until thickened.
Pour into desired serving dishes.

title: tomato shake
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 20 seconds.

title: broccoli surprise
directions: In 2 1/2 quart casserole, mix together first 6 ingredients. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place back in oven until cheese melts. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken creole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter until onion is tender but not browned.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, bay leaf, sugar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to boil; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and heat.
Blend cornstarch and water and stir into mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add parsley.
Serve on hot cooked rice.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, skin side up.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350° . Easy and different and tastes sweet and spicy!
Serves 4.

title: cynthia's dip for chips
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix with other ingredients.
Heat through and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Preheat in oven just until cheese melts.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: This equals 9 cans condensed soup.
Combine 1/3 cup mix with 1 cup water; heat until thick.
This equals 1 can soup.
You can saute onions, celery or mushrooms to add to the reconstituted mix.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, pudding mix and milk, then stir in Cool Whip.
Layer the mixture in large Pyrex dish with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Garnish with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: 7-up bundt cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar for 20 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour; mix well.
Stir in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour into a well-greased 12 cup Bundt or tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Make sure to grease and flour cake pan before you put in cake batter.

title: banana fizz
directions: Blend bananas and milk in blender.
When bananas and milk are blended, add soda and stir to mix.
Pour into 4 glasses and serve.

title: pork crown roast
directions: Season roast and place in shallow pan in preheated 325° oven. Wrap bone
tips
with
foil
to
prevent
overbrowning. Roast, uncovered, 2
hours.
Saute
celery and onion in butter about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Season ground meat (or use the pkg. of chili mix). Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar, oleo, cream style corn, jalapeno (more if desired), and onion. Add milk if necessary.

title: stir-fry chicken and veggies
directions: Cut chicken into narrow strips.
Melt margarine in skillet or wok (medium heat). Add chicken, pepper, onion and celery. Toss while cooking. When chicken changes color (from pink to white), add dressing and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat. Stir often. Cook about 30 minutes. Good over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken breasts genovese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine garlic, basil and olive oil in a blender or food processor.
After processing, add salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Split chicken breasts lengthwise and spread with basil mixture and close.
Dip each breast in egg mixture and roll in mixture of bread crumbs and flour.
Heat 1/8-inch olive oil in skillet and saute breasts on each side until golden.
Place breasts in shallow baking dish; bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over meat (I use this marinade for all kinds of beef, roasts and steaks).
Place in a clear plastic bag.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Turn bag occasionally to distribute marinade. Remove meat from bag; reserve marinade.
Grill meat outdoors or broil in oven, basting with reserved marinade.

title: wiener and cheese crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Split the wieners to within 1/2 inch of each end.
Insert 3 strips of cheese into each slit.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Wrap dough over wiener, keeping cheese up.

title: sausage cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Chop onion.
Saute slowly in butter.
Combine muffin mix, egg, milk and corn.
Put in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole.
To onions, add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spread over corn meal batter.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until brown and set.
Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Cook rice in water. Fry chicken breast in oil until lightly browned.
Bring soup and milk to boil. Add broccoli and chicken to soup mixture. Spoon over rice.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into thin strips and place on bottom of roasting pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top, then mushrooms and mushroom soup, then pour red wine on top.
Cook at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in covered roasting pan.
Stir every 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles with sour cream on the side to add to individual taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
If too dry, add water.
Bake at 350° until brown.
tags: Stove Stop corn bread stuffing mix

title: walk-away taco
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients together and drain.
Add salsa.
Heat beans and add.
Add salsa.
Place on bottom of dish or tray.
Add ground beef on top of beans; grate Cheddar cheese and put in oven to melt.
Spiral sour cream and more salsa on top.
Add olives and avocado to decorate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Press ingredients firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: sawdust pumpkins (or any shape)
directions: Mix all ingredients and let children mold a pumpkin with a stem or any other holiday creation.
Allow to dry one full day and then paint.

title: chocolate chip melt-aways
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at low speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt; add to butter mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, add chocolate morsels.

title: creamy shrimp stuffed potatoes
directions: Cook, then drain, frozen chopped spinach.
Season with
1 part mayonnaise and 2 parts margarine.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix ingredients except beets in saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Remove and pour over beets.
Let stand 6 hours in refrigerator. Enjoy!

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Combine oil, molasses, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in long pan (this will be thin).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until light brown. Combine all ingredients and bake in large casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Broccoli should be used without thawing).

title: baklava
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes the 2 cups sugar, honey and lemon juice.
Mix together the nuts, 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Melt the butter.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and butter together.
Add rice and water.
Place half of the mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pieces of boneless, skinned chicken on mixture.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 275° for 3 hours. Serves 8 people.

title: mom's special meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 4 ingredients, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, 2 teaspoons mustard, salt and pepper.
Form loaf and place in greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taquitos
directions: Drain gravy from roast beef.
Heat and break up roast beef and corned beef.
Add cumin.
Warm tortillas.
Place spoonful of meat in center and roll up tightly.
Glue end of tortillas with paste made from flour and water.
Fry Taquito in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 30 Taquitos.

title: korean appetizer meatballs
directions: Shape into balls the size of large marbles.
(Refrigerate or freeze if done ahead.)
Arrange meatballs (thaw, if frozen) on shallow pan and bake at 500° for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Reserve meat juices.
Serve meatballs good and warm.
Serve with Horseradish Sauce Dip.

title: thanksgiving candlelight punch
directions: Chill the apricot nectar and Sprite. Just before serving time, combine the apricot nectar and concentrated orange juice in the punch bowl. Slowly pour in chilled Sprite. Add peaches and float generous spoonfuls of ice cream on top of the punch. Serves 35.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix 4 1/2 cups water, soup mix and boil for 7 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and sausage into boiled mixture.
Place into large casserole bowl and bake covered for 1 hour on 350°.

title: pancakes deluxe
directions: Preheat griddle to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine egg, sugar, butter and milk; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just to blend; batter should be slightly lumpy.
Bake on preheated griddle for 1 to 2 minutes per side. For thinner pancake, a little more milk can be added.

title: nine day slaw
directions: *May substitute 1/2 teaspoon celery seed for diced celery.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In large roasting pan, combine popcorn and nuts.
Place in 250° oven while preparing glaze.

title: squash telfair(squash, southern style)
directions: Clean squash.
Boil whole squash until tender; drain.
Cut lengthwise in halves and place in glass baking dish.
Cover squash with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (soft).
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili special
directions: Cook meat
and
onion
in
a
skillet
and
drain.
Add Chili-O powder
and
simmer another 10 minutes.
While cooking the meat
mixture, start another large pot (8 quarts); add V-8 juice, chili
beans
and
mix
tomatoes plus the water in pot. Bring to a boil then reduce to low heat.
Add the cooked meat mixture to the big
pot
mixture
and
return to a slow boil. Then turn to simmer
and add Armour chili and cook another 10 minutes.
One cup of cooked spaghetti can be added also at the time you add the Armour chili.

title: orange cappuccino cheesecake(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine nuts and 2 tablespoons sugar and butter; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Increase temperature to 450°.
Next, beat together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and flour in large bowl. Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Blend in sour cream. Dissolve coffee powder and cinnamon in orange juice.
Add juice mixture gradually to cream cheese mixture until blended.
Pour over crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 250° and bake for 1 hour.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim.
Refrigerate.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar.
Garnish as desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with sliced potatoes, onion and carrots.
Then add ground beef.
Layer the vegetables and then the beef.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook for 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over top of casserole. Return to oven just until cheese melts.

title: good salad dressing
directions: Blend oil, vinegar and sugar in blender for at least 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and blend for another 3 to 4 minutes.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes; stir.
Cover and bake until macaroni is tender, about 20 minutes longer.

title: charleston shrimp pilau
directions: Fry bacon crisp; cook onion in bacon fat and add tomatoes and rice.
Mix well.
Cover; heat to boiling, then simmer 20 minutes, stirring.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes for rice to get fluffy; add shrimp and bacon and put in dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Melt margarine and mix with
dressing.
Place
on casserole dish a thin layer of chicken, onion,
celery,
salt and pepper.	Mix mushroom soup and
cream of	chicken and 1 can of chicken broth.
Pour over and top with the herb dressing.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Stir milk and sugar into large pot; bring to a rolling boil over medium heat. Boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat; add margarine, vanilla and chocolate chips. Stir until smooth. Fold in nuts and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: jiffy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Add flour gradually, mixing until dough is thoroughly blended.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Fit into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cut dough into 1 x 4-inch rectangles.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: southern corn bread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix bread.
Add raw eggs and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Have dressing soft, about consistency of cake batter or thick soup (really soupy).
(This is secret to good dressing; it will cook dry.)
This degree of consistency was the hardest for me to learn.
Bake in greased baking dish, 13 x 9 1/2-inches for about 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours before serving.

title: sloppy joe mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spoon into cracker crust. Combine
last
4 ingredients over low heat.
Stir until all is melted and spread over pie.
Chill and serve.

title: baked egg "brunch"
directions: Cube bread but do not remove crust.
Mix bread, cheese and dry mustard.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
In a saucepan, melt margarine and pour over corn flakes.
Stir until moist.
Spread over bread mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat coffee cake
directions: Stir vanilla into sour cream; set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts and cherries in small bowl and set aside.
Cream margarine and regular sugar until light; add eggs and beat until light.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Put 1/2 batter in greased Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of nut and cinnamon, etc.
mixture on top of batter.
Layer rest of batter mixture and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
For best results have eggs and sour cream at room temperature.

title: orange sugared pecans
directions: In small heavy saucepan, combine the sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat to 234° (soft ball stage), stirring occasionally. Add butter and orange peel.
Stir to blend.
Add pecans. Stir to coat good.
Spread on wax paper or greased cookie sheet. When the coating is firm, gently break pecans apart.
Store in covered container.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine first with butter, then with other ingredients, except crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients, if pork chops are not covered, add more liquid.
Cook on low all day.

title: baked beans plus
directions: Place a layer of sliced onions in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Add 1 can of beans and arrange 4 slices of bacon on top. Spread about 1/4-inch layer of catsup over the bacon.

Place a second layer of onions on top and form another layer with the other can of beans, 4 slices of bacon and catsup. Top with a layer of bacon, onions and catsup. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Cook in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: texas stew
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients together.
Brown ground meat and add to liquids.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan.
Top with can of Hormel chili.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Spread jalapenos and black olives on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until hot.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a large saucepan, blend first 4 ingredients with 10 cups of water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and salt.

title: very own soda
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass and serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on the box. Combine spinach (drained), onion and stuffing mix; mix well and add seasonings. Melt butter (do not get hot); pour over stuffing mixture. Add eggs and cheese. Mix well; roll into walnut-size balls. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix thoroughly at least 200 strokes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients well. Put in pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried mustard chicken
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Combine the bread crumbs, flour and paprika.
Combine the mustard, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 2 tablespoons water; melt the butter.
Line a shallow pan with foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip the chicken breasts in the mustard mixture, then coat them with the crumb mixture.
Put in the prepared pan.
Drizzle the butter over the chicken.
Bake until browned and cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bell pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with water; add salt and bring to boil.
Cook until tender.
Pour mixture in strainer and drain.
After it has stopped dripping, return to pot.
Add vinegar and sugar; bring to boil and cook for about 30 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Cut Delicious apples into 1/4-inch slices.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops on both sides in hot oil.
Place apple slices in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Top with pork chops. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours. Enjoy!
Serves 6.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves lengthwise.
With a teaspoon, carefully remove yolks to a small bowl.
Set whites aside.
Mash yolks until fine and crumbly.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, vinegar and sweet pickles.
Mix well.
Fill white halves with yolk mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind or chop all and mix in 3 tablespoons salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, drain and rinse well.
Mix sugar, water, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Mix and boil 5 minutes; fill jars and seal.

title: no pardon pie crust
directions: Melt oleo in pie pan.
Mix sugar and flour, then stir in pie pan and press out.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Combine eggs, margarine and sugar. Add gelatin, coconut and applesauce.
Blend well.
Pour into pastry shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yields 2 pies.

title: cherry pie filling
directions: This is for a
pound
can
of
frozen cherries with sugar. Add approximately 4 quarts of water, less can be used. Bring this to a boil.
Mix
clear
jell
with sugar and enough water to make a paste.
Add
to
cherries.
Let boil 1 minute. Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: easy chili con queso
directions: Melt first three ingredients in microwave.
Keep warm in a chafing dish and serve with your favorite salty munchie! (We prefer light and crispy Fritos!)
Easy and delicious!

title: meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Break egg into bowl and beat slightly. Put all other ingredients into bowl and mix well.
Shape mixture into balls.
Arrange in a baking pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Mix pineapple with juice, carrots, broth and raisins in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork and serve.
Makes 9 servings.

title: hamburger and green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain well, then add the green beans, tomato soup, water, salt and pepper.
Turn in large casserole.
Cook the potatoes in boiling water until soft.
Mash while hot and add enough milk to make fluffy, yet stiff to hold shape.
Drop in mounds on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
(Instant potatoes work well!)

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix first three items and pat into bottom of 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together rhubarb, sugar and Jell-O.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Spread rhubarb mixture in bottom of pan.
Arrange marshmallows over rhubarb mixture.
Pour cake batter over other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mother's southern fruitcake
directions: With electric mixer, beat the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, buttermilk and remaining ingredients.
Grease several pans.
(I put mixture in 1-pound Crisco cans; makes a beautiful gift wrapped in Saran Wrap and tied with ribbon.)
Bake cake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes if small and 60 to 90 minutes if large pans.
Check with cake tester.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk with sugar in a saucepan; heat to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and stir until marshmallows and chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mushrooms and rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
Add other ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Make a paste of sugar, cornstarch and flour and some of the cold milk.
Scald rest of milk and blend with paste.
Stir until thick.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add egg yolks and cook for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Remove and add vanilla.
Fill baked pie crust; cover with meringue and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Spoon out onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: glorified onions
directions: Slice onions extremely thin, then marinate overnight in large bowl with vinegar, sugar and water.
Drain and toss with mayonnaise and celery salt.
Serve with crackers or bagel chips as an appetizer.

title: little smokies
directions: Wrap bacon around hot dogs; broil and turn as needed.
Bring next three ingredients to boil.
Add 1 small onion (chopped) and 1 tablespoon horseradish mustard.
Simmer five minutes.
Pour over smokies.

title: old fashioned sauerkraut and kielbasi
directions: In large skillet, mix together first 4 ingredients with small amount of liquid if needed.
Place kielbasi on top.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Remove kielbasi and place in oven loosely covered for 25 minutes at 325° (optional).
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Then add all other ingredients, ending with cheese.
Serve over chips.

title: banana split
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of margarine and mix with graham crackers.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: baked limas
directions: Bring limas to a boil in water.
Add salt and sugar.
Reduce heat and cook slowly until limas are very tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Drain beans.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in butter and catsup.
Bake at 350° until limas are delicately browned and crusty on top (about 1 hour).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma linda's coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg, margarine, milk and cream cheese with mixer.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moist. Pour 1/2 batter in 8-inch pan, bottom greased only.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir mixture and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: okra pickles
directions: Pack okra tightly into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Place a garlic clove and a hot pepper in each.
Combine water, vinegar, pickling salt and dill seed in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour boiling vinegar mixture over okra, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yield:
7 pints.

title: macaroni and ground meat
directions: Mix ground meat, onion (chopped), green pepper (cut up in pieces) and 2 teaspoons salt.
Brown.
Drain off grease.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 cup of water.
Cook until done.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix macaroni in sauce.
You can also add oregano and mushrooms.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream sugar and oleo in bowl.
Add eggs and milk; mix well before adding pineapple.
Just before baking, pour mixture over bread cubes in a separate bowl; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a large greased casserole dish.

title: baked asparagus with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to hot (400°).
In a buttered baking dish, arrange a layer of asparagus, dot it with butter and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cover the asparagus with slices of cheese and sprinkle with a little of the grated Parmesan cheese.
Alternate layers of asparagus and cheese, ending with a layer of sliced cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Sprinkle with melted butter. Bake until cheese is melted, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: molded spinach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water, vinegar, mayonnaise, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Blend well with rotary beater.
Pour into tray for refrigerator freezing. Quick chill in freezing unit without changing control for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm, about 1-inch from edge but soft in center.
Turn mixture into bowl and whip with rotary beater until fluffy.
Fold in spinach (thin small pieces), cottage cheese, celery and onion.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm in refrigerator (not freezing unit) 30 to 60 minutes.
Unmold and garnish with salad greens and optional tomato wedges.
Serve with additional mayonnaise.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand until bubbly.
Stir in oil, salt and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Form into a ball and knead on lightly floured surface for 5 minutes, adding flour as necessary to make soft, sticky dough.
Place in lightly oiled bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until three times in bulk (3 to 4 hours).
Punch dough down.
Roll out on floured surface to a 12-inch circle.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Cover and chill until served.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Let potatoes thaw until easily separated, about 30 to 40 minutes.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, onions, chicken soup, sour cream, butter and cheese.
Mix thoroughly and turn into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with potato chips and bake at 375° for one hour.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: pheasant count et fatre
directions: Brown pheasants in oil.
Place in a casserole dish.
Pour brandy over and ignite.
Add carrots, onions and herbs.
Cover and cook 90 minutes at 320°.
Remove pheasants.
Add cream to gravy and serve over the pheasants.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter. Add broccoli and stir.
Add water, flour and cheese.
Beat eggs well and add.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, mace and salt.
(Mix soda in buttermilk.)
Blend into dry ingredients oil, eggs and buttermilk. Add pineapple, coconut, nuts and carrots.
Bake 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: suz best cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bring to boil pineapple and sugar.
Pour over hot cake and allow to cool.
Mix pudding according to directions, let set until firm, then spread over cool cake.
Cover with sliced bananas. Spread thawed Cool Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped pecans.

title: low-cal oven fried chicken
directions: Mix the crushed cereal, salt and pepper together on a flat plate. Dip chicken pieces into milk, then roll them in the cereal mixture. Place them, skin side down, on a nonstick cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. Turn and bake on other side 30 minutes.

title: raw sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs and potatoes.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly and pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings.

title: julekake(norwegian christmas bread)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, fruit, raisins and cardamon in large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix yeast with warm water (8 ounces). Add to flour mixture.
Melt butter and add to flour.
Mix well and knead.
Let rise to double in size (overnight).
The next day, knead on floured surface.
Divide into 4 loaves, place in greased loaf pans and let rise one hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and brush with melted butter and sugar.
Return to oven for 15 minutes longer.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use 1/3 cup mix in a large mug and fill with hot water.

title: bread sticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Slowly add flour.
Mix well until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise until double. Roll into pencil-like strips.
Place 1/4-inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.
Brush with oil and sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch freezer dish.
Freeze.
Will keep up to 3 weeks in the freezer.
Makes 20 servings.

title: governor's egg casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add the cheese and stir until melted. In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, make layers of sliced eggs, cheese sauce, potato chips and bacon.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be refrigerated and baked next day.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange 6 slices of bread in bottom of approximately 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover each slice with cheese; top with remaining bread.
In a separate dish, mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until puffy and lightly browned.
Serve with bacon and fried apples.

title: diabetic raisin cookies
directions: Put seedless raisins through food grinder and combine with water.
Mix and sift together the flour, salt and soda and add to raisin mixture.
Add melted margarine and Sucaryl and mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and dates until it forms a soft ball. Add nuts and beat until real creamy.
Form a loaf in a wet cloth. Now, mold into a loaf.
Let cool overnight and slice.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat
a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray. Set aside.
In
a large bowl, combine carrots, sugar, pineapple, prune puree, egg whites and vanilla. Stir to blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients except coconut.
Mix completely.
Gently stir in coconut.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake about 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Cut into 3 x 3-inch squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: blueberry or peach or cherry delight
directions: Crust:
Mix with mixer the oleo, flour, 1/4 cup granulated sugar and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: swiss steak
directions: Steps 1-4)
Trim excess fat from meat; cut into small serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Place meat on bread board; sprinkle with half flour mixture; pound it into meat using rim of saucer (etc.).

title: molded salmon appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese and soup (undiluted) in a double boiler. Heat and stir until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in water according to package direction, then add to soup mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Bend well.
Pour into 5 cup mold. Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold.
Serve with fresh vegies and crackers.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Brown hamburg; drain off fat.
Put remaining ingredients in pan and bring to a boil, add hamburg and cook 10 minutes. Add 1 can stewed tomatoes and 1 large package of frozen vegetables or Veg-All in can.
Add 1 cup orzo and finish cooking until orzo is done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine eggs, salt, sugar, flour, pineapple with juice, soda, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Mix together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: mandarin orange salad(serve at a "coffee")
directions: Twelve hours before serving, mix marshmallows, sour cream and pineapple.
Fold in oranges.

title: german sweet and sour green beans
directions: Brown bacon and then saute the onions.
Stir in flour.
Add water, vinegar and bean liquid.
Stir in the rest of the seasonings, bringing it to a boil.
Add the green beans and heat through.
Pour into serving bowl and top with crumbled bacon.

title: honey cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Beat in honey, egg and vanilla.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Roll in 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured pastry canvas.
Cut cookies with floured cookie cutter. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.

title: coconut cream eggs
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and coconut.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Shape into eggs.
Chill overnight before covering with chocolate.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: To save time I chop the vegetables in a food processor. In a large bowl, combine all the vegetables, then sprinkle the salt over them and cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain. In a large pot, combine the sugar, vinegar and spices; bring
to a
boil.
Add the vegetables.
Return to a boil and lower
heat. Simmer
minutes.
Pack
into
hot sterilized jars,
leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims and cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield: 4 half pints.

title: carrot cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Frost when fully cooked with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Add together dry ingredients and add it to zucchini mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until it forms ball in cold water; place marshmallow cream into syrup.
Stir until well mixed.
Stir in pecans; pour out on greased wax paper or cookie sheet.
Can be formed in log or in candies.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Bake cornbread in a medium pan.
Let cool.
Crumble cornbread into pan.
Add pinto beans, onion and green pepper.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice together, then pour over the first four ingredients.
Top with tomato and bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown meat and cook onion in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Stir now and then. Serve over hot cooked egg noodles. Serves 4.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Make white sauce:
Melt 2 tablespoons fat and stir in flour. Add milk and broth and cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Season with salt and pepper.

title: 2 step broccoli chicken divan
directions: Arrange chicken and broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: sunny citrus fizz
directions: Place fruit juices and sugar in blender container and process 10 seconds to dissolve sugar.
Add sorbet and process on low speed until sorbet begins to blend into mixture.
Increase speed to high and blend just until smooth.

title: triple treat fudge cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 18 muffin cups with baking cups. Combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg and stir.
Combine in separate bowl cream cheese, sugar and eggs; stir in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups 1/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Spoon brownie mixture evenly over cream cheese mixture until cups are 2/3 to 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until brownie is set. Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: greek-style potatoes
directions: Arrange all the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with salt, pepper, rosemary and paprika.
Put in oven and stir vegetables as soon as the butter melts.
Stir and baste occasionally as potatoes bake. Bake 1 hour until potatoes are cooked through and golden brown at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream-raisin bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, soda, salt and brown sugar in a large bowl; cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Combine sour cream and remaining ingredients in a large saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture is thickened.
Pour over prepared crust.
Sprinkle with reserved topping mixture; gently press topping mixture with fingertips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cover and chill 4 hours or until firm.
Cut into bars.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix together and stir until smooth the pudding and milk. Refrigerate for about 15 minutes.
Butter sides and bottom of a Pyrex baking dish.
Line bottom and sides with graham crackers. Keep whole.
Fold in Cool Whip with pudding mixture.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Put in second layer of crackers. Spread remainder of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Top with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate.
Best when made the night before.

title: mexican tamale pancakes
directions: Condiments:
1 to 1 1/2 cups each shredded Cheddar, chopped green onions including tops, chopped tomatoes, sour cream and prepared taco sauce or salsa.

title: honey balls
directions: Dough is made with flour and water.
Knead together real good and then start to roll dough and make little balls.

title: cinnamon crunch snack mix
directions: Combine the margarine, honey, orange juice concentrate and cinnamon in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds; add the cereal and stir to coat.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until the cereal no longer looks wet.
Serve hot or cold.

title: crisscross potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Score in cross.
Bake until nearly done, pour melted butter over and bake until crisp.

title: island macadamia nuts
directions: Melt margarine and add soy sauce.
Toss nuts gently to coat. Bake at 400°, stirring often for 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook until thick. Stir frequently to keep from sticking. Put in jars and seal. Can place spices in white cloth and remove before placing in jars. Will get the flavor, but not whole spices in the catsup.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Cut or break up angel food cake into pieces and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and evaporated milk, then spread mixture over the cake.
Top creamed mixture with fresh strawberries or fruit of choice, then top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: e-z tuna casserole
directions: Soak
ham overnight.
Change water several times.
Heat oven to 500°.
Put
cups hot water in cooker with ham.
Put in oven and cook for 25 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Leave ham in oven for 4 more
hours.
Turn	oven
on again and cook for 25 minutes.
Turn oven
off
again.
Do not open oven until cool (overnight).

title: fiesta chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch cubes. Brown in 2 teaspoons oil, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce and corn.
Stir in chili seasoning.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups rice and chilies. Remove from heat and let stand 7 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix egg whites, honey, oil and warm water to dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Place rice, soup and milk in greased dish (9 x 13-inch).
Stir well.
Place chicken, uncooked, on top of mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Cover with foil so it's airtight.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: creamy pineapple pudding
directions: In large casserole dish put a layer of the wafers, then the mixture until all the mixture is used.

title: macaroon balls
directions: Mix, roll into balls and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Combine first four ingredients, mix until blended.
Add meat and blend lightly but thoroughly.
Form meatballs, about 1-inch diameter.
Arrange in a single layer in large baking pan.
Put into slow oven (275°) and bake, uncovered, about 15 minutes.
Turn once during baking.
If you don't have chafing dish or heated pan to serve, turn to lowest setting and keep warm while serving others.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes about 175 appetizers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix orange juice, 7-Up and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Add fruits and mix well.
Pour into individual molds or servers and freeze.

title: hot mexican corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, salt, and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half the batter into a hot greased 10 1/2-inch cast iron skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with half the cheese.
Pour remaining batter over cheese, top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375 for 35-45 minutes.

title: mozzarella lasagna(this is good for people who don't like ricotta cheese.)
directions: In large pan, brown ground meat and drain well.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
