Stir in chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, pepper and water.
Cover and cook, over low heat, approximately 30 minutes.
Mix often to prevent sticking.

title: quaker meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for one hour.
Drain; let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: white moon cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure; add baking powder and salt and sift 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly until fluffy. Add flour mixture alternately with milk, a little at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla; fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased 9-inch cake pans in a 325° oven for 15 minutes, then increase heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: jello pretzel dessert
directions: Roll pretzels coarsely.
Add soft oleo and 2 teaspoons sugar. Put in 10 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 375°, then cool.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Heat milk in double boiler or microwave.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes.
Add 2 beaten eggs to hot milk and stir.
Add gelatine and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Tear cake into small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cooled liquid over cake.
Spread with whipped topping and top with cherries.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, 1 1/2 cup sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture until well blended. Refrigerate dough for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in flat open bowl.
Shape dough into 2-inch balls and roll in cinnamon-sugar.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.
Freezes up to 3 months.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in order given.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with taco chips.

title: broccoli, cheese, rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
In a large bowl, mix broccoli, celery and onion.
Add Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and rice.
Pour all into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
May top with grated cheese.
Very good with baked ham.

title: cucumber sandwich spread or dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add salt, pepper, lemon juice, onion and mayonnaise. Beat until smooth. Peel cucumber and dice very fine. Drain well. Fold cucumbers into mixture.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients; store in covered jar or container.
When ready to serve, place 1 tablespoon of mixture in 1 cup of boiling water.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cool whip together.
Shake dry jello into mixture and mix.
Add drained fruit and chill before serving.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add milk and pudding. Beat until thickened. Put into pie shell and top with Cool Whip. Shave chocolate bar over the top. Refrigerate.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Heat until melted first 3 ingredients.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Melt chips in double boiler and spread on top.
Chill.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Break up pretzels and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat butter until melted; pour over pretzels.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, stirring twice.
Cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: mimi's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Return to stockpot. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add oregano, thyme and Italian seasoning.
Simmer and let marinate several hours with lid on. Serve over angel hair pasta.
Add a salad and garlic bread for an awesome meal!

title: irish christmas cake
directions: In a large glass bowl, soak fruit and brown sugar in tea and whiskey overnight.
Set oven to 300°.
Grease three 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Mix together flour and spices; add to soaking fruits, alternating with beaten eggs.
Add baking powder last.
Mix well. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. When cool, brush tops with honey to glaze.
(May also prepare in one 10-inch tube pan and bake for 3 hours.)

title: six bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with salt & pepper.
Add onion and continue browning.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients including juice from beans.
Heat up.
Put in casserole, bake at 350° until juice is cooked down and not soupy, 45-60 minutes.
Serves 16-20.

title: pineapple-pecan cheese ball
directions: Toast nuts in shallow baking pan 7 to 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Coarsely chop 1 cup toasted nuts; set aside.
Chop remaining nuts until ground.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients well with spoon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo.
Remove from heat and add sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour and pecans.
Bake in greased pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Gradually add milk to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight or several hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and American cheese slices.
Let cream cheese soften and then add to other cheeses.
Dice small onion into small pieces.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix all together.

title: shrimp rockefeller
directions: Boil or steam shrimp, then drain off any water.
Mix shrimp with creamed spinach.
Mix in 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese and 4 to 6 ounces sharp cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice tomatoes in wedges and place around edges of dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining Mozzarella.
Top with a light sprinkling of Parmesan cheese or fine bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°. Place under broiler for 1 minute to brown top lightly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Place chicken and water in a covered saucepan; cook over medium heat until tender.
Remove chicken, debone and dice. Chill broth, remove congealed fat from broth.
Place 2 cups of the broth, chicken and remaining ingredients, except cornstarch and rice in saucepan.
Cover and cook over low heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining 1/4 cup broth.
Stir into chicken mixture, continue cooking until thickened.
Divide equally into 4 portions.
Serve each portion over 1/2 cup hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello-angel food cake
directions: Follow directions on box for making the cake.
Mix desired amount of Jell-O to flour before other additions.
Use 1/3 to 1/2 box of Jell-O.
Bake according to box directions.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Cook the first 2 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Set aside and cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill 4 hours, then freeze. (When you want some, just take out of freezer and let thaw enough to cut.
Put back in freezer.) This is a great dessert for low-fat dieters if the maraschino cherries are omitted.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Cut jalapenos in half lengthwise and remove seeds, place in paper towel to remove juice. Mix together all ingredients, and spoon into halved jalapenos. Refrigerate in covered container for 2 hours. Serve.

title: hand biscuits
directions: Sift flour; cut in shortening and add milk slowly, stirring until dough is soft and moist.
Knead lightly.
May be patted out 1/2 inch thick and cut with a cutter or pinch off balls of dough and roll in hand; flatten as you place in pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix last 5 ingredients for dressing.
Pour dressing mixture over vegetables.
Let stand at least 12 hours. Will keep a long time.

title: wild rice
directions: Melt butter. Add all ingredients except chicken broth.
Cook about 15 minutes or until rice turns yellow (medium heat). Add broth and season with salt and pepper.
Put in buttered casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Stir just until all the ingredients are moistened.

title: quick chili dip
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, over low heat, combine all ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring frequently. Serve hot with chips or sliced fresh vegetables. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: meat balls
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and cranberry sauce is melted, then pour over meat balls.

title: pork chops and rice(a quick meal)
directions: Sprinkle garlic salt and pepper over pork chops.
Brown on both sides in electric skillet.
Leave in pan.
Slice onion and place a slice of onion on each pork chop.
Sprinkle rice over pork chops and add tomatoes.
Dissolve bouillon in water and pour over pork chops.
Cook at 300° slowly for 45 minutes to 1 hour until rice is tender.
You may have to add more water as they cook.

title: buffet green bean salad
directions: Mix together anchovies, mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and onions.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drain green beans well.
Toss with dressing and let stand, covered, in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Serve garnished with egg yolks and whites and cherry tomatoes.

title: cherry angel roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake following package directions.
Divide batter into 1 medium pan.
Spread evenly.
Cut through batter with knife or spatula to remove large air bubbles. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until set.
Immediately invert cake onto towels covered with confectioners sugar.
Remove foil carefully.
Immediately roll up each cake with towel jelly roll fashion.
Cool completely.
Fold cherries, coconut and cherry juice into topping.
Unroll cakes and spread with filling.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package.
Add frozen limeade diluted to make 1 quart.
Do the lemonade also the same way.
Put in freezer and freeze.
Just before serving add the ginger ale. May add ice cubes if you like.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Make certain it is thoroughly blended.
Add eggs and vanilla and blend. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal.
Grind raisins and dates.
Add with coconut and chopped pecans or walnuts to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake 10 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Cookies will fall flat when removed from oven.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients; add snow to taste.

title: cherry dessert(quick and easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place marshmallows in bottom of margarine greased pan.
Boil sugars and milk to soft ball stage.
Add margarine and beat.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over marshmallows while hot.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix and roll into 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick sheet.
Cut and place individual pieces on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with corn meal.
Allow to rise to double size.
Bake 7 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Turn and bake 7 additional minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Slice onions and celery fine (chop in food processor) and cook in covered pan in butter until transparent and tender (don't burn).
Pare and dice potatoes or slice in processor.
Add with broth to onions and celery.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Put through food mill or food processor. Before serving, add cream and heat until "piping" hot.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix water and butter in 12 x 8-inch baking dish until butter is melted.
Stir in stuffing mix (in the canister) and 1/4 cup salsa.
Arrange chicken over stuffing.
Pour remaining salsa over chicken.
Cover with foil.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press in bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: my basket bread
directions: "I will rain bread from Heaven for you."
Exodus 16:4.

title: fudge walnut brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large mixing bowl.
Blend well, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until springs back from touch.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then thoroughly prick warm cake with tester or wooden pick completely through to bottom of cake.

title: fried pancake chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except vegetable oil and pancake mix.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Pour pancake mix in a brown paper bag.
After 1 hour of marinating chicken, drop each piece in paper bag.
Shake vigorously to coat pieces thoroughly.
Drop each piece in skillet of hot oil.
Cook over medium heat until well done.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar in 1/2 cup water for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut extract.
Punch holes in cake with toothpicks. Pour syrup over cakes.
Wrap in Reynolds Wrap when cool.
Let stand for 3 days, then freeze.

title: best ever fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a large saucepan; let boil 6 minutes only!
Mix other ingredients in a large pan or bowl; pour hot mixture over it.
Stir well, but do not beat.
Pour into buttered pans and let cool.
This makes 5 pounds of super-delish fudge.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Cook pudding according to directions.
Layer graham crackers, pudding and bananas to fill Pyrex dish.
Top with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.
Slice and serve.

title: almond joy
directions: Stir together syrup and coconut.
Let set for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and almond bark.
Roll coconut and syrup in balls and dip in chocolate.

title: quick and easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: quick & easy chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with the milk according to the directions on the package.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9x13 pan, place one layer of crackers.
Put 1/2 of the pudding/Cool whip mixture on top of the crackers. Repeat - another layer of crackers and then the remaining pudding mixture. Place a third layer of crackers on the pudding mixture.
Microwave the frosting 30-45 seconds and drizzle over the crackers in criss-crosses.
I use only maybe 1/2 to 2/3 of the can.
Refrigerate overnight for best taste.

title: macadamia nut cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup milk, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup nuts, salt and vanilla in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and scald.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup milk, egg yolks and cornstarch and add to hot milk mixture.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat egg whites with remaining 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Carefully fold into milk mixture and turn into pastry shell.
When cool, top with whipped cream and sprinkle with additional chopped nuts, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork.
Add 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer until tender. Combine sugar, cornstarch, pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork; stir until gravy thickens.
Add pineapple chunks, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Serve with extra soy sauce.
Serves 6.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Whisk egg slightly.
Add mayonnaise and soup; blend.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour int oblong 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs evenly over top.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: nut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar, water and syrup in a 2-quart casserole. Microwave 12 to 14 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir in nuts. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until light brown. Stir coconut and vanilla into syrup.
Microwave on High for an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until hard crack stage is reached. Add baking soda. Stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Spread to 1/4-inch thickness. Cool. Break into pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in pie plate.
Mix last 4 with blender and pour over top and bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate fudgy fig cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until cracks come, don't overcook.

title: squash with cheese sauce
directions: Cut squash; cook in salted water until tender; drain and place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Melt margarine. Add salt, flour and milk; cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Add grated cheese; stir until melted.
Pour sauce over the squash and mix slightly.
Top with breadcrumbs; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a moderately hot oven until top is brown.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Make jello according to package.
Drain fruit well.
After jello sets, stir in drained fruit and cranberry sauce.
Chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and chile powder. Stir in tomato sauce, vinegar, catsup, corn syrup and 1/2 cup water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir in orange liqueur.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Makes 3 cups.

title: seven layer mexican dip(be sure to make a lot of this recipe - it is great!)
directions: Mix mayo, sour cream and taco mix.
Layer all ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch pan (bean dip, mayo mix, green chilies, lettuce, Cheddar cheese and tomatoes).
Serve with tortilla chips.
For additional layer, you can use guacamole, but it cannot be saved.

title: jewel crown dessert
directions: Heat until warm 1 box lemon jello, pineapple juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until syrupy, about 20 minutes.
Mix 2 small or 1 large package Dream Whip according to box directions.
Fold syrupy jello into Dream Whip.
Fold in jello squares.
Line tube pan with one package ladyfingers. Lay a few in bottom of pan.
Pour mixture into a pan.
Chill for 3 to 5 hours. Slice and serve.

title: nacho platter
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Combine avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper in food processor until smooth.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and mix with cream cheese, pepper, onion, lemon juice and hot sauce.
After mixing well, roll into ball or log.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top.
Chill.

title: aunt ina's congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add marshmallows, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Whip Dream Whip and mayonnaise and spread on top of the congealed salad.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top of whipped cream.

title: crisp waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Beat eggs with hand beater until fluffy; beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
Pour batter from cup or pitcher onto center of hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops, about 5 minutes.
Remove waffle carefully.
Makes three 10-inch waffles.

title: cinnamon-scented cookie cutter ornaments
directions: In a large saucepan mix together cornstarch and baking soda. Gradually add water.
Cook mixture over low heat, stirring occasionally.
The mixture will slowly get bubbly, then thicken. Stir constantly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and turn clay onto aluminum foil.
It will thicken more after being removed from heat.
It will be cool enough to handle in minutes. Knead in cinnamon.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine onion, red wine, bread crumbs, flour and consomme in casserole.
Put in meat.
Cover casserole.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: bunsy's spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain; set aside.
Dice tomatoes, cucumbers, onion and bell pepper.
Mix spaghetti and vegetables together.
Pour Italian dressing and Salad Supreme; mix well. Chill in icebox for approximately 1 hour.
Serve.

title: clinch mountain vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour and water in double boiler.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Just before removing from heat, stir in margarine and lemon extract. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: orange sherbet cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in 4 pans.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Crush crackers.
Combine with butter.
Press in bottom of pan. Melt marshmallows in milk; cool.
Fold in whipped cream, vanilla and chocolate squares.
Let stand several hours.

title: easy kolacky
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese thoroughly.
Blend in flour and mix well.
Roll into about 8 balls.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheets.
Liberally sprinkle working surface with powdered sugar.
Place 1 ball of dough at a time (keep remainder refrigerated) on sugar and roll into a large square.
Cut dough into squares 3 inches each or whatever size you wish.

title: swordfish in sour cream
directions: Saute shallots and mushrooms until soft; set aside.
Add wine to mushroom liquid and add swordfish.
Cook 10 minutes per inch, turning once, about 2 minutes.
Before fish is done, add sour cream.
Surround with shallots and mushrooms.
Continue cooking until done, but be careful not to boil sauce.
Serves 4.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash 2 cups strawberries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and mashed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Fold remaining berries into cooled mixture.
Pile into pastry shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend in blender.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Lasts 3 to 6 months.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper in separate bowl.
Pour over green beans.
Add half dried onions and mix in green beans.
Sprinkle the other half over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: scotcharoo's
directions: In a saucepan, combine Karo syrup and sugar and cook over medium heat until it starts to boil.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Put in Rice Krispies and stir until coated.	Press slightly into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Melt bits (do not cook) and spread on top.
Let it firm up and cut into squares.

title: tofu lasagna
directions: Saute onion in butter; add chopped mushrooms and cook slightly.
Set aside.
Boil noodles; then drain.
Drain tofu and mash; add to onion and mushrooms along with spices.
Spread enough spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to cover.
Layer noodles, tofu mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
After last layer of noodles, finish with sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheeses are golden brown and sauce is bubbly.

title: hungarian stew
directions: Brown meat and onions in vegetable oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes on floured board.
Divide dough into 12 even pieces, shape in balls and put in greased round 8-inch pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, peppers and beef. Spread about 1 tablespoon onto tortilla and roll up. Then slice about 1/2-inch thick.

title: preacher's wings
directions: Bake wings at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt margarine and stir in remaining ingredients.
Coat cooked wings with sauce.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Put in a bowl.
Mix around in bowl to coat pieces with flour, then add to batter, mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Tastes great with vanilla ice cream!

title: tomato french dressing
directions: In covered jar or shaker, combine ingredients.
Chill.
Shake well before using.
Serve on salad greens.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pickled beets
directions: Clean and cook beets.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over cooked beets.
Cook another 15 minutes.
Pack in jar and seal.

title: breakfast bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar. Combine oats, flours and wheat germ. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: steamed cranberry pudding
directions: Mix well and put in a greased angel food tin with foil over top.
Steam in a large roaster for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Top with sauce.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and softened margarine for 15 minutes at low speed on mixer.
Medium speed for hand mixture.
Spread over cooled crust and add bananas and crushed pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and black pepper.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add red and green bell pepper, green onions and corn to eggs.
Add 1/2 cup cheese to mixture.
Add flour mixture.
Put into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until brown.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix vegetables, chicken and soup in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until well mixed.
Pour into pie plate over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon chuck steak(barbecue)
directions: Score fat edges of meat.
Place in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over steak.
Let stand 3 hours at room temperature or 6 hours in refrigerator, turning steak several times.
Remove steak from marinade.
With paper towels, remove excess moisture.
Cook over hot coals about 12 minutes on each side for rare or 15 minutes on each side for medium.
Brush occasionally with the marinade.
Carve meat across grain in thin slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese-bran bread
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream together the margarine, egg and sugar.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture the buttermilk.
Fold in the bran cereal and cheese.
Spoon into well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lazy day fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple with vanilla pudding.
Add fruit cocktail, lemon pudding, and mandarin oranges.
Fold in 1 large container of whipped topping.
Chill and serve.
Makes a large bowl full.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in a mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Mix flour and soda.
Add to first mixture and beat again.
Add apples and pecans; mix well.
Bake in tube type pan which has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
(Bundt pan is also good to bake in.
Good without icing.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks (save whites for meringue), sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add salt and milk.
Mix well.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour while hot into browned pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
When stiff, beat in 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Top pie and brown in 350° oven.

title: mexican dip
directions: *Or, use 2 cups Monterey Jack cheese with jalapeno peppers for a hotter taste.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix together ingredients in small bowl.
In a skillet, place vegetable oil or melted butter or spray with Pam.
Drop from spoon into a skillet.
Fry until brown, then flip over and brown other side.
If using grease, blot on paper towels and serve.

title: meatballs in sour cream sauce
directions: In large bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, Parmesan cheese, milk, onion powder, garlic salt and pepper.
Form into 20 meatballs, using a rounded tablespoon for each.
In large skillet, brown meatballs in oil; drain excess fat.
Sprinkle meatballs with paprika; add onion.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes. In medium bowl, combine gravy and sour cream; pour over meatballs. Heat slowly, basting meatballs frequently.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, baking soda, powder, sugar and salt.
Mix with buttermilk, oleo and eggs.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Boil the cranberries in enough water to cover them. Cook until all pop open. Then add the sugar. Boil until thick. Skim off white foam.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix butter, flour and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat until fluffy. Add milk, vanilla and coconut. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm and golden brown.

title: cherry-pineapple dessert
directions: Cook together until thick the cherries, sugar, pineapple and tapioca.
Then mix together remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle half this mixture in a baking dish.
Pour in cherry mixture and place remainder of crumb mixture on top of filling.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salt baked roast
directions: Wipe roast with a damp paper towel.

title: cheese spread on half buns
directions: Mix all together, spread on each half of bun.
Bake on cookie sheet in oven at 350° until cheese is melted and golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: jello angel food fruit cake
directions: Mix jello according to package directions, mixing in fruit and using juices of thawed fruit or berries to equal water needed. Lightly grease a 4-quart bowl or cake pan. Cut up cake into 2-inch squares. Alternating cake and jello, fill container. Refrigerate until set, approximately 3 hours. Whip the cream and use it to frost the jello cake after it has been turned out onto a serving dish.

title: mrs. boyer's shortcake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350°.
Can add fresh fruit to this cake before baking. Bake in a 9-inch baking pan.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in uncovered casserole dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in flour and oil.
Knead on slightly floured board for 3 minutes.
Place dough in buttered bowl, turn to butter top, cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down and on floured surface roll into size of your pizza pan.
Bake at 425° oven for 5 minutes.
Add your pizza toppings, then bake for up to 10 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together spinach, mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Add French fried onions.
Put remaining onions on top.
Bake in a 300° oven about 30 minutes or until hot.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: In microwave, brown ground chuck in covered dish for 5 minutes.
Stir, adding onion and bell pepper.
Season with oregano and garlic salt with parsley to taste and cook, covered, for an additional 5 minutes.
Place English muffins in pan, sprinkling Parmesan cheese over each.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of tomato sauce over each muffin.
Top
with ground chuck mixture, about 1 tablespoon more tomato sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in regular oven for approximately 10 to 15 minutes at 450°, or until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt butter, stir in chocolate wafers and press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool; add creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into shell. Freeze.
As served, garnish with whipped cream.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Add all ingredients (except chicken) to melted butter.
Stir to mix.
Add chicken and marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Barbecue or bake at 325° for 45 minutes, basting often.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain, reserving liquid; set aside. In the same kettle, saute onion in the butter until transparent or soft. Stir in salt, pepper and flour. Gradually stir in milk, stirring constantly, until thickened. Gently stir in cooked vegetables. Add 1 cup or more of reserved liquid, depending on desired thickness.
Heat thoroughly. Serve. Makes about 2 1/2 quarts. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Boil sugar, water and butter until it reaches soft ball stage. Add vanilla and pecans.
Stir to coat.
Pour onto waxed paper and separate and cool.
Delightful!!

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Blend in hot water and cool.
Add egg and stir well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kahula
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in
gallon glass jug.
Shake and blend well.
Shake jar once a day.
Store in dark place 3 to 4 weeks. Strain Kahlua and place back in jug.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer; place in refrigerator until cool.
Take off grease and take chicken out.
Debone.
Heat chicken broth up.
Add soups. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add chicken. Mix with cooked spaghetti.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spray an 8-inch round baking dish with nonstick spray coating. In a large mixing bowl beat eggs and egg whites until foamy. Beat in milk, honey and vanilla.
Stir in bread cubes.
Pour into the prepared baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. To serve, spoon warm pudding into dessert dishes.

title: cantaloup cooler
directions: Remove cantaloup seeds and scoop out pulp.
Puree all ingredients in blender except ice cream.
Add ice cream and blend just long enough to mix.

title: jeanette's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together.
If you have time and energy, separate the egg; add the yolk to the mixture and lastly, fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Bake on hot griddle.
Serves 2.

title: curried cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook in small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain well.
In a greased 2-quart dish, combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and cheese. Add cauliflower and blend.
Toss bread crumbs with melted oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, stir in blueberries. Pour into a greased bundt pan and bake one hour at 350°.

title: fried potatoes with egg
directions: Slice the cold leftover potatoes.
Fry with the onions in the hot shortening.
When nicely browned, stir in the eggs, add salt and pepper.
Fry a few minutes longer until eggs are cooked. Good breakfast or light supper dish.
Add a little ham if desired. Serves 4-6.

title: bean salad
directions: In large bowl, gently mix together kidney beans, Northern beans, tomato, onion and parsley.
Squeeze lemon juice over the mixture.
Add olive oil and gently toss bean mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and cornstarch.
Add eggs, melted butter and evaporated milk.
Add vanilla, salt, pecans and coconut. Pour into uncooked pastry shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° until firm to the touch in center of pie.

title: amen for leftover turkey or chicken
directions: Cook broccoli to crisp-tender.
Place turkey in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with broccoli, top with cheese and cover with mixture of milk and soup.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover with onion rings and bake 5 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
(Freezes well.)

title: broccoli fruit salad
directions: Mix broccoli, grapes, bacon, onions and almonds; set aside. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and raisins.
Refrigerate both mixtures separately overnight, then mix together.

title: minestrone hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, cabbage, tomatoes and water.
Heat to boiling.
Add rice.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and simmer 1 hour. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Combine items in a microwave casserole bowl.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and minced garlic (optional).
Heat in microwave for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: ham bread
directions: Drain ham thoroughly and flake apart.
Mix together with mayonnaise, sour cream, margarine, garlic salt and parsley flakes. Split and half bread.
Place bread on foil lined baking sheet. Spread margarine on bread.
Place sliced Mozzarella over margarine. Spread ham mixture over Mozzarella and top with grated cheese. Heat in 400° oven until bread is heated through and cheese is melted.
Ham bread can be topped with olives, green peppers, onions, etc., if desired.

title: celebration rice
directions: Melt margarine in 4-quart Dutch oven. Saute green onion and carrots in melted margarine.
Add rice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is opaque.
Add bouillon, thyme and water. Cook over high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in parsley. Serve.
Serves 12.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in thin slices.
(Do not pare.)
Slice onions in thin rings.
Cut peppers in fine strips.
Dissolve salt in ice water and pour over sugar and spices and bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat to boiling point.
(Do not boil.) Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Pour chicken broth over stuffing mix. Combine all other ingredients except soup and cheese. Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: beet wine
directions: Cut beets fine; add water to cover and cook until tender. Drain well and let stand until next day.
Add sugar to one gallon beet juice.
Add enough black pepper that will stay on a ten cent piece.
Cook for 10 minutes.
When the beets and water are warm like milk, pour through a cheesecloth.
Add the yeast spread on toast and 1 tablespoons raisins.
Set in a warm place 10 days, then put through cloth again.
Bottle it and in 10 days it is like Port wine.

title: cumin beans
directions: Pour beans into pot and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and beans are hot.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce with meatballs
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs, stir in bread crumbs, cheese, salt (1 teaspoon) and dash of pepper.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breast and onions. Drain. Cut up. Heat broth and butter. Add flour, stirring constantly. Add salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes. Add chicken, evaporated milk, onion and cut up eggs. Put into casserole and top with crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream(vanilla)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 1 can Eagle Brand and mix.
Pour 2 more cans of Eagle Brand, Carnation and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in container.
Fill rest of container with regular milk.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in the approximate order they are given, then press it all into 1 big greased loaf pan, or use 2.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chef salad
directions: Wash and dry all vegetables.
Break up lettuce.
Cut up cucumbers and tomatoes.
Add in string beans.
Cube Mozzarella. Dice all the meats.
Toss everything together.
Add dressing. Toss again.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Put everything in large bowl and let marinate at least 12 hours.

title: stroganoff
directions: Melt butter; add onion and brown.
Add meat, flour, paprika, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in mushrooms, soup and sour cream.
Simmer at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugars, vanilla and milk.
Beat eggs, then add to the mixture.
In a separate bowl,
combine flour, soda and salt. Add this slowly to the creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake on a cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: butter tarts
directions: Pastry for 12 medium tarts. Combine all ingredients and beat well. Fill tart shell 2/3 full. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Lower to 250° for 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the ingredients together in order given.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add flour, lemon extract and 7-Up. Beat again. Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: apple cheese bread pudding
directions: Combine cream, eggs, applesauce, brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Lightly toss bread, cheese and nuts.
Place bread and cheese mixture in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour cream mixture over bread mixture.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes or until bread is completely saturated.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let cool at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: darwin's apple crunch
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan, spread the apple filling. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over apple filling.
Slice butter into strips and place over the cake mix.
Sprinkle the walnuts or pecans over entire mixture; bake at 375° for 1 hour or until cake is golden brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
In large iron skillet, add meat grease.
Let grease and pan get warm on burner.
Add cabbage and salt and water.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender, approximately 15 minutes.

title: peggy's spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add other ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Bake 20 minutes in greased muffin pans at 350°. Fill the cups 3/4 full.
Does not need to rise, just refrigerate and use at will.

title: egg rolls
directions: 1. To ensure the right consistency of whipped cream, chill the beaters and bowl in freezer before beating.
The cream should be well chilled too.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the onions and meat.
Add mushrooms, salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and flour.
Blend well and bring to a gentle boil in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Combine milk and biscuit mix; stir until smooth and pour over meat mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes, uncovered, at 425°, then spread with sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven another 5 minutes.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Blend sugar and egg white thoroughly. Add pecans. Drop on cookie sheet
by tablespoons. Bake 30 minutes at 275°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend together cake mix, 2 eggs, oleo and pecans.
Pat into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and remaining egg.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased loaf pan; bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half, leaving seeds in place.
Place in microwave, cut side down, punching the skin in several places and cook on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Take seeds out.
Put the melted margarine mixed with the white wine into each half.
Sprinkle each half with 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon.
(Optional:
Fill cavity with the mushrooms after the added cinnamon.)
Cover and cook about 4 to 5 minutes on High.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: sports event chili(crockery cooking)
directions: Brown beef and stew meat in corn oil; add onion, bell pepper, garlic and saute until soft.
Skim off excess grease.
Add beans, tomatoes, jalapeno, cilantro, cumin, black pepper, chili powder, oregano, salt and green chilies.
Simmer at least 2 hours.
Line 4 large bowls with tortillas and spoon chili into each.
Top with Cheddar cheese and onions.
Can be made before game starts.
Watch game while chili cooks.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown ground turkey, green pepper and onion; drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until thoroughly heated.
Serve on buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy no-bake peanut butter fudge cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over oats.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cookies will firm as they cool.

title: black and white frozen shakes
directions: In a blender for each shake, combine 3 squirts chocolate syrup, 1/2 pint ice cream, 2 cups skim milk and 4 ice cubes. Blend on high until smooth and icy. Serve with straws in soda fountain or other tall glass.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour batter in pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pears and use juice to heat and dissolve jello and gelatine.
After jello is dissolved, add cream cheese and stir to melt.
Then add pears that have been mashed fine with a fork.
Add nuts and Cool Whip with gelatine and pears.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into mold to congeal.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients then add cooked rice and tomatoes. Pour all into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, egg, sugar and milk together in mixing bowl.
Add melted butter.
Stir crushed crackers on top.
Stir; pour into buttered baking dish (2-quart size) and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jacqi's apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Peel, core and slice apples into ovenproof casserole.
Melt stick of margarine.
Add flour, sugar and vanilla.
Sprinkle apples with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with crumb mixture.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes, until juice bubbles up.

title: peaches 'n cream pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients except whipping cream and peaches with a wire whisk or hand beater until well blended.
Pour by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle (grease griddle if necessary).

title: glazed fruit dessert
directions: Drain the pineapple and mix juice and pudding until thickened. Fold in pineapple chunks, oranges and bananas.
Refrigerate until serving. Garnish with Cool Whip.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jambalaya grits
directions: Heat bacon grease in a heavy skillet.
Gradually add flour, stirring constantly, until roux becomes light brown.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Cook for 5 minutes.
Cook grits according to package directions.
Add to roux.
Add tomatoes and ham. Sprinkle with bacon and serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: avgolemono soup(greek lemon soup)
directions: Cook chicken with onion and garlic in chicken broth 25 minutes.
Add rice and simmer until done.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Cut cheese in chunks and melt in double boiler.
When completely melted, add remaining ingredients.
If not thick enough, add either flour or cornstarch and water.
Better when made a couple of days in advance and should be kept warm while serving.

title: rummy steak marinade
directions: Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic, rum, ginger, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 teaspoon season salt in a medium mixing bowl. Mix well. Shake remaining pepper and season salt on steaks. Pierce steaks repeatedly with fork. Place in shallow pan. Pour marinade over steak. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 6 hours. Grill. Enjoy!

title: apple pound cake
directions: Coat nuts and coconut with 2 tablespoons flour and mix well. Add apples, nuts, coconut and flavoring. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a bowl, stir cornmeal, flour, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, stir egg, buttermilk and onion.
Mix liquid into cornmeal until dry mixture is moistened.
In skillet, add enough oil to make 1/2-inch.
Drop batter by tablespoons into oil.
Fry until golden, turning once.
Makes 24.

title: cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In medium bowl, stir together flour, sugar and cream until the dough forms a ball. Turn dough out onto a surface dusted with flour. Fold dough in half and knead 5 to 7 times, adding just enough flour to keep dough from sticking to hands. Gently roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Using a 3-inch biscuit cutter, coat with flour. Cut dough and place on baking sheet coated with spray. Space 1-inch apart. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and bread together; add onion soup mix, sage, pepper, salt and seasoning.
Stir in eggs, celery soup, chicken soup and enough broth to make a very moist dressing.
Put in greased pan and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cream together the next 4 ingredients and ice when cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased dish for 30 minutes. Take out of oven, stir and return to oven.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: bacon roll-ups(appetizers)
directions: Melt oleo in water in saucepan; add to stuffing, mixing well. Add egg and sausage, mix well.
Chill 1 hour, then shape into pecan size shape.
Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Wrap each piece of stuffing mixture with bacon and fasten with a wooden pick.
Place on rack in a shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown and crisp, turning at halfway point in cooking.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients except milk.
Mix dry ingredients until they resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and blend until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured surface. Knead lightly and roll 3/4 inch thick.
Place on lightly greased pan and brush tops of biscuits with butter.
Bake in a very hot oven at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal peanut butter chocolate chips cookies
directions: Beat margarine and peanut butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Combine oats and soda.
Add to margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Add chocolate morsels.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet 5 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: mrs. martha's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Chip up chicken in baking dish.
Add one can of cream of chicken soup and 1 can of chicken broth. Place chicken mixture in baking dish.
Put milk in heated shortening and do not stir.
Pour into flour and mix, then crumble over chicken mixture.
Bake until brown on top for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: super simple chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in 6-quart pan with 3 quarts water, salt, pepper and garlic powder until done.
Remove chicken from broth and set aside.
Cut tortillas in half, then cut in 1-inch strips.
Drop into boiling broth and stir.
Mix 3 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water and add to dumplings to thicken.
Remove chicken from bones and add to dumplings.
Season to taste.
Try this, you won't believe it!

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 2/3 cup. Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour batter over butter.
Arrange peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place butter, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes (medium heat).
Place whole graham crackers on bottom of cookie sheet (approximately 4 dozen).
Pour hot syrup over crackers and sprinkle with chopped nuts and coconut.
Place in 350° oven and bake until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Take off pan immediately.
Place on well-greased aluminum foil.

title: guava chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Cook the next 5 ingredients until custard-like; keep stirring.
Remove from flame; add the gelatin mixture.
Mix
thoroughly and chill.
Beat
the
egg whites stiffly, then fold into the custard mixture.
Pour into a
9-inch baked
pie shell; refrigerate.
Top
the
pie
with whipping cream.

title: cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until they form peaks. Mix into the egg whites:
sugar, vanilla, almond extract, crackers and pecans.
Spread this "meringue" mixture into a 9 x 13-inch or similarly sized pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare Dream Whip and spread over the cooled meringue.
Drizzle the cherry pie filling over the top.
Serves 15.
(Best if thoroughly chilled before serving.)

title: tiny peas with celery
directions: Saute celery in butter until soft and transparent.
Do not brown.
Add peas, salt and pepper.
Heat just until hot.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain; saute onion in butter.
Add cut cheese and mushroom soup.
Simmer until cheese is melted; combine all ingredients.
Serve hot in crock-pot.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with bread. Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Set aside. Layer bread, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13 greased pan. Pour egg mixture over layer. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. May use bacon or ham in place of sausage.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Place chicken strips in pan and stir-fry in olive oil.
Place bell pepper strips and onions in also and stir-fry.
Place mixture in tortilla shells and add cheese strips.
Roll up and place in oven at 350° for about 15 or 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and add chopped tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: "mrs.  alexandra's" scotch shortbread
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Knead with your hands until dough cleans the bowl. Divide into 4 balls.
Flatten with hands on ungreased cookie sheet to 1/4-inch thick.
Prick with a fork.
Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 25 minutes or lightly browned.
Remove and sprinkle with sugar immediately and cut into wedges or strips.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Brown together beef strips, onion, garlic and oil.
Add ginger, green pepper, bouillon and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil and then stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: basil-marinated swordfish or salmon
directions: Marinate fish in sauce for 3 hours, turning several times. Remove fish and grill about 7 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Freeze cookie dough until firm.
Cut 1 package dough into pieces.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Pour into dish.
Cut remaining dough into slices, place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: banana-apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots until soft.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add apricots.
Cream shortening. Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 5 x 3 pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in 1 egg.
Sift and stir in flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Put in shaker and set aside the sugar and cinnamon.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: spiced tea(serves 4)
directions: Mix sugar and spices (tie spices loosely in cheesecloth bag) in hot water.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over tea leaves; steep 3 minutes.
Strain.
Add fruit juices and cold water.
Chill.

title: maggie's candy(peanut butter balls)
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add sugar and work with hands.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip each ball in paraffin mixture and place on wax paper.

title: bell peppers
directions: Peel eggplant, wash and cut all vegetables.
Warm oil; add all ingredients.
Simmer until soft, add salt and pepper.
Serve with steak.

title: vegetable chili soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients and put in a crock-pot and let simmer for 2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with cream.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Divide dough on lightly floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 10 minutes.

title: bettan's chicken
directions: Steam broccoli until cooked and place in a large buttered baking dish.
Over medium-high heat melt butter, season and cook chicken chunks.
Remove chicken chunks and set aside.
Combine sour cream, onion soup mix, and pan juices.
Spread half of the mixture over broccoli and top with chicken chunks.
Whip cream and fold into remaining amount of sour cream mixture, spread over chicken. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's minestrone
directions: Brown sliced onions in oil at bottom of large soup pot.
Turn off heat while you prepare and add all other ingredients, except pasta.
The beauty of this recipe is that you can include almost anything you have and like and the amounts do not have be exact. (*The starred vegetables are definitely optional.)

title: pecan  chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: seafood crescents
directions: Combine shrimp, cheese and onion.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Cut crescent rolls where separated, then cut triangle in half again down center.
Place a dab of seafood mixture at wide end of dough.
Roll toward point.
Pinch ends together and curve slightly to form a crescent.
Bake according to directions on crescent package.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Gently move stem back and forth until stem pops out of mushroom, leaving cap.
Brown sausage, adding chopped up stems.
Drain.
Return to stove, add cream cheese, Creole seasoning and hot sauce.
Heat until mixture is combined well.
Remove from heat.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oriental spicy slaw
directions: Break Ramen noodles into small pieces into a very large bowl; add cabbage and green onions.
Set aside.
Combine oils with Ramen seasoning packets, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss well making sure everything is wet.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours, tossing occasionally.*
Place mixture on serving platter and sprinkle with almonds and sesame seed.

title: everything vegetable soup
directions: Use the size can of vegetables for the amount of soup you want to make.
For fresh vegetables, add according to your taste. Whatever you don't like can be omitted.

title: bass with tomato sauce
directions: Place fish in a buttered baking dish and pour in the wine. Salt and pepper, cover and poach at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove the fish and the liquid.
Melt some margarine in the dish and stir in 2 tablespoons flour and the liquid from the fish.
Heat until thickened and add 3/4 cup milk.
To this, add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and boil gently.
Pour this sauce over the fish.

title: jim's cucumber slices
directions: Layer sliced cucumbers and onions in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour over cucumbers, cover, and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with slotted spoon. Keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: one dish casserole meal
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onion, then add remaining ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Saute the bacon, onion and garlic.
Add the catsup, brown sugar, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Add the beans last. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat egg whites until foamy and fold into mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° until pie starts to turn brown, then turn oven down to 250° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Slice green pepper into strips, slice onion into wedges and cut carrots into pieces.

In a large skillet (or electric frypan), brown chicken in oil over medium heat; add vegetables and stir. In a measuring cup combine reserved pineapple juice, wine vinegar, salt, brown sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken and vegetables; stir until well mixed.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes, stirring occasionally, until carrots are tender.
Add pineapple chunks and cherries.
Serve over rice.
Prepare the rice while dish is simmering.

title: turtle bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cup flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Heat water, milk and margarine to 125° to 130°; stir into yeast mixture.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Shape a 2-inch piece of dough into a ball for the head.
Shape 4 walnut-size pieces for the feet and 1 walnut-size piece for the head.
Shape the remaining dough into the body.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Press raisins into head for eyes.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Make crisscross cuts in shell.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: currant cinnamon biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Cut in shortening using a pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Make a well in the center and pour in milk and eggs. Mix quickly and lightly with a fork.
Add currants.
Turn dough onto a floured cloth.
Knead lightly about 7 times, turning dough each time.
Lightly roll dough 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into small diamonds.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar, mixed.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 24.
Best served hot.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cover cookie sheet with separated graham crackers.
Combine sugar, oleo and butter.
Cook for 2 minutes until dissolved. Sprinkle chopped nuts over graham crackers.
Pour sugar mixture over nuts and graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Heat soups in saucepan until warm.
Fry hamburger meat. Drain.
Pour soup mixture into meat; mix well.
Place 1 bag of Ore-Ida Tater Tots in mixture, burying them.
Place more Tater Tots on top for decoration.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are brown (about 30 minutes).

title: black bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 8-inch quiche pan or pie plate. Drain the can of black beans and spread on top of cream cheese. Cover beans with finely diced red onion. Cover with Raspberry Salsa. Top with shredded Pepper Jack cheese. Heat until bubbly, about 20 minutes, at 325°. Serve with tortilla or corn chips. Serves 20.

title: pizza burgers
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine hamburger, pizza sauce, oregano, red pepper, and garlic powder.
Spread a thin layer of hamburger mixture on bun halves.
Broil until meat is cooked, approximately 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put 1 slice of tomato on each burger and cover with a slice of cheese.
Return to oven and broil until cheese is melted.

title: merry cranberry freeze
directions: Mix together cranberries, sugar, pineapple and walnuts. Gradually add cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping into 1 1/2-quart bowl or lightly oiled 6 1/2 cup ring mold.
Freeze until firm.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water and bring to a boil, then add peanuts.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Turn fire out, add oleo, vanilla and red food coloring.
Beat until loses gloss, then spread on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Break like peanut brittle.

title: tossed taco salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add to salad.
Toss with dressing.
Makes a large salad.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef with next four ingredients.
Drain fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: creme de la creme
directions: Stir together gelatin and sugar.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin and sugar are dissolved (about 5 minutes of stirring).
Stir in the cream; chill until slightly thickened. Add sour cream and vanilla; beat until blended.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Unmold onto a serving plate and spoon over the cream.

title: fruited coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, toss
pears and apples with lemon juice. Add cabbage, carrots and raisins; combine well and set aside.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish well.
Soak bread in milk.
Mash carrots with butter.
Mix bread and milk with carrots.
Stir in eggs and sugar.
Bake for 1 hour or until well browned on top.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line twelve 1/3-cup muffin cups with paper liners.
Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy small saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until butter melts.
Cool until mixture is warm to touch.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Add milk mixture and stir just until blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Divide batter equally among prepared cups.
Bake until golden and tester inserted into center of muffins come out clean, about 20 minutes.
Transfer to racks and cool.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the dry vanilla pudding mix, undrained crushed pineapple and sour cream; mix until well blended.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Sprinkle with coconut. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.
Pour in mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° until golden brown and set.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix well. Pour into a large Ziploc plastic bag and add venison, beef or any meat you desire; seal. Turn several times to make sure the meat is covered, then allow to marinate in the refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours ahead of cooking, turning a couple of times. The tougher the meat, the longer you should marinate. Venison can marinate up to 4 days if quite tough. This recipe will handle approximately 6 steaks.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil in heavy saucepan for 2 minutes the first 4 ingredients. Add baking soda.
Pour over contents of 5 1/2-ounce bag of corn pops (they are hulless).
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: pizzella (italian cookies)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, baking powder, vanilla and margarine together.
Blend in flour and mix.
Make sure Pizzella griddle is hot before cooking.
Place a heaping teaspoon full on each griddle for about 30 seconds.
Close top for 30 seconds.
Peel off and repeat to cook the rest of the batter until finished.
Cool on rack then stack in piles.
To make Pizzellas not as crispy, decrease the amount of oil to 1/2 cup and use only one stick of margarine.
You can change the flavors for a different taste by adding anise, almond or chocolate.

title: polpette
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Form into balls and flatten slightly.
Brown in hot oil, in heavy skillet.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1-inch pieces.
Best served warm.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: golden fried peach pies
directions: Sift the flour into a bowl and cut in shortening.
Add enough water gradually to hold pastry together.
Press into a ball. Divide into 5 parts and roll each part on a floured surface into a 5-inch circle. Drain the peaches and mash.
Add the cinnamon and butter.
Mix well. Place 2 tablespoons peach mixture on each circle and fold over. Seal edges with a wet fork.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until golden brown and drain on absorbent paper.

title: buttermilk, wild rice and pecan pancakes
directions: Combine 3 cups water, wild rice and salt in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until wild rice is tender (about 40 minutes). Drain well.
Cool to room temperature. Can be prepared ahead a day or two.
Store, covered and refrigerated.

title: hershey bar layer cake
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Cream the next 2 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add mixture of milk, sugar and cocoa which has been boiled 5 minutes.
Add soda dissolved in water.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Frost with Hershey Bar Icing.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large microwave bowl. Heat until cheese is melted and broccoli is cooked.
(May need to start broccoli first.)

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash peppers and remove seeds and white portion. Peel onions and chop fine. Combine and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and salt. Add pepper mixture. Bring to a boil and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Pour immediately into hot sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Work the shortening with the back of a spoon until fluffy and creamy.
Gradually add sugar while continuing to work with a spoon until light.
Add the egg; sift together the next 5 ingredients and combine with raisins and nuts.
Heat applesauce to boiling point.
Add gradually to sugar and flour mixture.
Turn into about a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with beans.
Ready to serve.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and flatten with fork (dipped in water). Sprinkle with sugar. Bakes fast.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and pie shell. Cook in microwave at 2 minute intervals, stirring each time; usually takes about 8 minutes, depending on oven wattage.
When it becomes thick, add butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour in prepared pie shell.
Cool for meringue.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat well. Put on pie.
Put back in oven at 400° and lightly brown. Cool Whip can be used instead of meringue.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix butter into sugar and flour; add milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in 1/8-inch slices.
Cook in boiling water with onion until nearly tender.
Lift out of water with a slotted spoon and layer on bed of chips that have been prepared in a long casserole dish.
Grate cheese over squash and add pepper, if desired.
Broil or bake in oven until cheese is bubbly.
Salsa or picante sauce can be added as a garnish or may be added when served.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Wash and seed cucumbers (if skin is not bitter, leave on). Chop fine. Soak cucumbers for 15 minutes in vinegar solution (vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and salt); drain. Blend onion with cream cheese. Add drained cucumber and season to taste. Spread on crustless bread.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Mix in eggs and flour alternately.
Add flavorings.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Chill 4 or 5 hours.
Roll out thin.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water; cook until clear.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add berries. Refrigerate.
Pour into cool shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: chinese style vegetable medley
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add vegetables and stir. Cover; steam 5 minutes until crisp-tender.
Stir. Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Stir in 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat milk until lukewarm.
Add sugar and dissolve yeast cake. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 teaspoon salt and shortening.
Mix as for rolls adding enough flour to make firm dough.
For best results, let stand in icebox overnight.
Roll out on floured board.
Place on wax paper or cookie sheet to rise.
Fry in deep fat.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Serve on bread or on crackers.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Makes enough canape spread for 24 Melba toast rounds or dry, crisp crackers.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix baking soda to soup in the can.
Alternate flour mix with the soup mix.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting or butter frosting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onions until almost done, then mix rest of ingredients, except cheese, all together and put in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: date bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and shortening.
Blend thoroughly after adding vanilla.
Add the nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into bars when cool.

title: chicken and barley bake
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine onion, carrots, water, barley, bouillon granules, poultry seasoning and garlic.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Pour hot mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken thighs atop mixture.

title: buckeyes candies
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended.
Shape the mixture into balls, about the side of hickory nuts.
Place in refrigerator until balls are firm enough to hold a toothpick in them.
Melt 1 package of chocolate chips and 1/2 cake paraffin wax over boiling water.
Dip peanut butter balls with toothpicks into melted chocolate and then place on wax paper.

title: blue cheese puffs
directions: Melt margarine and Blue cheese in saucepan. Remove from heat. Cut biscuits into fourths.	Roll biscuit pieces into margarine and cheese mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven until golden brown. Serve warm!

title: saudi champagne
directions: Pour apple juice and Perrier into pitcher.
Float lemon slices and apple chunks.
Serve chilled in champagne glasses.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Use a 9-inch pie shell.
You can prepare your own favorite pie crust or purchase prepared crusts, your choice.
Cream butter or oleo until soft.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to cream until light and fluffy.
Slowly stir in corn syrup, honey, eggs, vanilla and 1 cup pecans.

title: karen's bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350° or microwave on High for 30 minutes.

title: tender heart tarts
directions: You will need a big bowl and a wooden board.

title: tastes like - apple pie ?  ?  ?
directions: Boil together sugar, water and cream of tartar just until it comes to a boil.
Add crackers and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle spice on pie.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until crust is browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash about 10 minutes with a little sugar and salt. Drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots. Fold in squash.
Mix melted oleo and dressing.
Put 1/2 of this in bottom of casserole.
Spoon veggie mixture on top, then rest of dressing. Mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, zucchini, salt, pepper and egg yolks.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into zucchini mixture.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into about 1/4 inch hot oil in skillet; brown both sides.
Serve immediately with catsup.
Makes 15 pancakes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese several hours before using. Mix well with Cool Whip; add sugar, vanilla and strawberry juice. Pour into pie crusts. Let set about 3 hours before cutting.

title: bean and pea salad
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over salad.
Let stand overnight or at least 3 or 4 hours before serving.
Drain before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Pour over baked cake; add chocolate chips and pecans and remaining batter. Bake 25 minutes more.

title: rye beer bread
directions: Heat beer to lukewarm.
Add salt, shortening and molasses.
Mix both kinds of flour together.
Make a hole in middle and pour in liquid mixture.
Let raise until double in size.
Knead and let rise again.
Makes 3 large loaves.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(One can sliced apples may be substituted for fresh apples.)
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: corn and tomato relish
directions: Combine everything, except water and cornstarch, in a large pan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 or 40 minutes.
Stir water and cornstarch, blending well.
Add to mixture, stirring for 5 minutes or longer until slightly thickened.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cook in water bath for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 pints. Simply delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add zucchini and everything else.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pans.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
