Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: sugar and spice cake(beer cake)
directions: Cream butter until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Combine flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with beer.
Mix until silky smooth batter is achieved.

title: quicky pork pie
directions: Arrange slices of cold pork in bottom of a casserole.
Season with minced onion, sage, pepper and salt.
Over this place a layer of hard-cooked eggs.
Repeat until dish is nearly full.
Pour a cup of leftover gravy.
Top with pastry.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until pastry is done, about 20 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all together and pour over salad.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain most of liquid off green beans.
Put both cans of mushroom soup into baking dish with lid and blend together.
Add green beans and stir until mixed with soup.
Add about half of onions and mash in with spoon, do not stir.
Cover and cook at 350° in preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Remove, add rest of onions to top and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes until onions are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 10.
Can be reheated.

title: party punch
directions: Select one fresh from the market, not too green, but tender and healthy.
Handle gently for they bruise easily.
Sweeten with smiles.
Blend with patience, humor and a pinch of mischief.
Do not beat.
Preserve over a steady fire of warmth and affection. Like fine wine they mellow with age.
Do not pickle or put in hot water.
This makes them bitter.
Serve with sugar, spice and tender-loving care.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into melted chocolate mixture.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended. Stir in flour and pecans.
Spread on greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.

title: mama's easy fudge
directions: Melt Creme Drops with water in double boiler or microwave. Add peanut butter and stir well. Spray dish with cooking spray and pour fudge in to cool. Cut in small pieces to serve.

title: veal chops with sage
directions: In a pan large enough to hold the chops, put the butter and sage; saute.
Add chops.
While the chops are getting fried, sprinkle salt on both sides.
Then add the flour and the Marsala. Simmer until chops are tender.

title: grandpa's best biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening (if using butter or margarine, should be chilled, not room temperature). Stir in cold milk.
The dough can have a few lumps; this is what gives the biscuits a flaky texture.
Roll out on a floured board to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Flour the biscuit cutter before cutting each biscuit.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and place in a preheated oven.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes (or until brown) at 425°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown on top.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift together and stir into first mixture the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough if desired.
Roll into small balls; roll balls in a mixture of 4 tablespoons sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Set aside 1/3 of dried beef.
Combine rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into ball, roll ball in dried beef. Refrigerate.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moistened; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 (9-inch) prepared round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.

title: bette clark's peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake until brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs together and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion. Add chiles and soup. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Fritos.
Pour in meat mixture.
Top with Fritos.
Bake at 350° until set. Top with cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Halve and grill (broil) the tomato or dry-fry it.
The tortillas should be slightly dry; stale ones are ideal.
Cut them into strips about 1/2 x 2-inch, deep-fry them until they are crisp and brown.
Set them aside.
Pour off all but
a tablespoon of lard or oil.
Fry the onion and garlic until golden brown; in a blender, puree them with the tomato.
Return the mixture to the frying pan with another tablespoon of lard or oil; fry until thick, stirring constantly.
Add the broth; simmer for 1/2 hour. Season to taste; pour over the crisp tortillas in individual bowls.
Serves four.

title: light and tender rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Add to milk mixture.
Stir in egg.
Gradually add enough flour to make soft dough.
Cover with a towel; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Turn out and knead lightly.
Shape into rolls.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair torte
directions: Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mix.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with a layer of graham crackers.
Put half the mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers. Put the rest of the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Frost the top layer with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate.
Good eating.

title: churchman stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cut steak across grain into strips and add to onion.
Cook over low heat until beef is brown.
Pour in bouillon and cover with lid.
Let simmer for about 1 hour or until tender.
Make sure liquid does not boil out.
Stir in mushrooms and let cook for about 5 minutes.
Add flour to the beef mixture to thicken the sauce for gravy, using water if more gravy is needed.
Add sour cream; stir.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles or rice.

title: john logiurato's spaghetti and meatball sauce
directions: Place hamburger in a large bowl.
Add egg, bread crumbs, parsley, cheese, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix with hands thoroughly and form into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
In a large Dutch oven with about 3 tablespoons olive oil, lightly brown meatballs and then remove.
Leave enough drippings to cover the bottom of the pan and discard the rest. Add the 3 cans of tomatoes and 3/4 can of water from puree.
Bring to a boil, gently add meatballs and stir.
Add garlic cloves, about 10 small sprigs of parsley, 1 tablespoon cheese, oregano and bay leaves; add the sugar.
Stir and simmer about two hours.
If the sauce gets too thick, thin with a little water.
If you have too many meatballs, put to the side and freeze.

title: poppy seed cake(yields 1 cake)
directions: Beat all ingredients together at medium speed for 5 minutes. Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan, inverted.
Enjoy!

title: sweet-n-sour delight
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch chunks. Brown in oil. Reduce heat to low. Add onion and garlic. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Add carrots and green pepper. Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into skillet; mix.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: daiquiri
directions: Shake thoroughly with cracked ice until the shaker frosts. Strain into cocktail glass.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers for 24 hours in lime water.
Drain and soak four hours in salt water.
Drain and rinse.
Soak 2 hours in clear water.
Cover with alum and water and bring to a rapid boil.
Drain and rinse.
Place in vinegar, sugar and spices.
Cook 30 minutes. Pack in jars and pour juice over pickles.
Seal.

title: hansel and gretel's gingerbread treats(5 dozen cookies)
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening with sugar. Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar. Beat well. Stir together dry ingredients and blend into molasses mixture. Chill about 3 hours. On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thick. Cut with a cookie cutter. Place 1-inch apart on a greased cookie sheet. Use candy red hots for faces and buttons. Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes. Cool slightly, then move to racks for cooling. When cool, you can pipe trim on cookies.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray a 9-inch square pan with vegetable oil spray.
In a mixing bowl, combine oil, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add oats, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix until blended.
Press mixture evenly and firmly into pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion together.
Drain off fat and add margarine.	Cut
up
potatoes
into
small pieces and add along with salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat in the frying pan on top of the stove for about 30 minutes or until potatoes are done. Top
with
cheese; put lid back on until the cheese melts.	If you
like
ketchup, you can add a little after you put it
in your plate.
If this sticks while cooking, just add a little water.

title: halloween cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and continue beating for 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and milk, alternating with flour and other dry ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350°.
Cake is done when it pulls away from sides of pan.
Decorate with candy corn while still hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots, walnuts, coconut and pineapple for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased pan for 55 to 60 minutes.
(This is a large cake.)

title: brandy rum cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly butter a 12 cup Bundt pan. Mix flour, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
In another bowl beat butter and sugar with electric mixer 5 to 8 minutes, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla, rum and lemon.
With mixer at low speed add flour, about 1/4 cup at a time, alternating with the sour cream and apricot brandy.
Scrape into prepared pan and smooth the batter. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Place pan on wire rack to cool completely.
Slice thin to serve.
Should have 26 slices.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients;
add grated carrots and mix well. Bake in 2 round (9-inch) cake pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until a little tender.
Add flour, milk and chicken broth.
Stir until mixed slightly.
Simmer for 10 minutes or more.
Stir in cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: venison casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion and ground venison.
Place 1/2 of meat into a Pyrex dish.
Add 1/2 of tomatoes or paste, then 2 cups potatoes.
Add a layer of cheese.
Repeat.
Beat eggs and pour on top of cheese for a crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is formed.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in a lightly oiled skillet; sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup fried onion rings.
Spoon mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange pork chops over mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold ingredients in Cool Whip and spread over cooked, cooled crust. Chill.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Cut in 15 squares. Excellent and easy!

title: 3 step cheesecake recipe
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Top with fresh fruit; drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted Kraft strawberry jelly, if desired.

title: swiss chocolate dessert(four layer dessert)
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and nuts.	Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine flour and sugar; add oleo, mixing well.
Pat dough out in a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put croutons on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Brown sausage.
Cut and place on cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate.

title: grandma's bread
directions: Mix together the shortening, yeast, sugar, warm water and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add 3 cups of flour and stir together. Add 1 cup flour and then turn onto floured bread board or pastry cloth.
Knead for about 5 minutes, adding flour until it is no longer sticky.

title: ice cream salt beef rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Rub roast well with black pepper.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and rub in well.
Place a 2 inch layer of salt in pan and sprinkle lightly with cold water.
Place roast in pan.
Pyramid salt on roast until covered with thick layer of salt.
Sprinkle with cold water so that salt will stick.
Cook 12 minutes per pound.
When done, remove and let cool 20 minutes.
Break salt crust from roast with hammer.
Slice and serve with vegetables.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add cream cheese, continue beating.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Fold in flour with spoon until moist.
Beat with mixer for about 2 minutes.
Bake approximately one hour and 20 minutes at 300° to 325° in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until crisp-tender. Saute onion in butter.
Combine with carrots, soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Top with croutons, tossed in butter.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated through.

title: dough for fried apple pies
directions: Mix well and add more flour to roll dough.
Pinch off small amount and roll to size of coffee lid.
Can use coffee can to cut dough.
Put cooked, dried fruit in center and use fork to press dough together.
Drop in hot shortening and fry.

title: lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and put in refrigerator until it begins to jell.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
When mixture is cool, mix with jello and place in dish that has been cooled in refrigerator.

title: no-fat "fried" chicken
directions: Cover baking sheet with foil and lightly coat with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine all ingredients except chicken and buttermilk.
Skin, bone and pat dry the chicken.
Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Then roll in dry mixture and place on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kitty litter cake
directions: Prepare cake mixes according to directions.
Prepare pudding and chill until ready to use.
Crumble cookies.
Set aside all but about 1/4 cup.
To the 1/4 cup of cookie crumbs, add a few drops of green food coloring and mix with a fork.
When cakes are cooled crumble in a large bowl.
Toss with half of remaining cookie crumbs and chilled puddling.
(Use only enough pudding to moisten.)

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cheese; blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze at least 6 hours or overnight.
Take from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken cutlets parmesan
directions: Dip each cutlet in egg first, then in bread crumbs. Fry each cutlet in hot olive oil.

title: shrimp pinwheel casserole
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender but not brown. Blend in flour and salt. Add tomatoes and cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Add cheese; stir until melted. Add shrimp and peas. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Top with Pinwheel Biscuits. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are done and golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: "dry" champagne punch
directions: Place all juices in punch bowl.
Add rum, wine, champagne and club soda.
Stir lightly with ladle.
Makes 35 to 40 punch cup servings.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Skim
fat from the turkey broth and measure, putting it back into
the roasting pan.
For each cup of gravy, measure 2 tablespoons
flour;
blend
and
cook until frothy.
Add 1 cup broth
for
each
cup of gravy.
Add seasonings and cook until thick.
Add
the gizzards that have been chopped and 3 chopped eggs.
Serve hot over dressing.

title: rice casserole
directions: In deep skillet brown and drain sausage.
Add pepper, onion, soup mix, water and rice.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole bowl.
Top with almonds.
Sprinkle with paprika and black pepper.
Bake in oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Almonds will be toasted.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to boil; add bouillon cubes and dissolve.
Add tomato juice, cabbage, celery, green beans and onion flakes.
Cook until done, then let simmer.
Eat any time.

title: pizza bites
directions: My children did not like to eat hard-boiled eggs until I made it a little more fun.
I kept a couple of pointed permanent markers in the kitchen.
After I had boiled the eggs, I would draw a happy face or flower on it, or write Good Morning, Have a nice day or whatever.
I put a bowl of water on the table and let them peel it, wash it off, then eat it.

title: dip for apples
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray 13 x 9-inch Pyrex with Pam and spread in pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out of center clean.

title: low-fat baked chicken(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: triple cheese chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water according to package directions; drain well.
Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimiento, skim milk and basil. Lay half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half each of the soup mixture, cottage cheese, chicken, American cheese and Parmesan cheese; repeat layers of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining American cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 2 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Makes 10 servings.

title: crispie treats
directions: Melt marshmallows, peanut butter, margarine and salt in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Pour over combined cereal and candies, tossing lightly until thoroughly coated.
With greased fingers, gently shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Place on waxed paper; cool at room temperature until set.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Spray bread pan with cooking spray and pour mixture into pan. Bake at 425° until center springs back when touched and top is brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat the white sugar and eggs together until creamy.
Add the vanilla, coconut and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown around the edge. Cool on sheet.
Yields 60 cookies.

title: cold tomato soup
directions: Blend.
Chill and serve with sour cream and sprinkle of dill.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package label directions; drain. Prepare seasoning mix, according to package directions.
Mix with the ground beef, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add 1 1/4 cups water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer half the macaroni, half the cottage cheese and half the meat sauce; repeat.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes, or until bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: banana-pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together the dry ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Do not beat. Pour into a greased round tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cake will crack a little on top.
Place the pan on a rack to cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased pan with bread slices.
Whip eggs and milk.
Place meat over bread.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Place shredded cheese on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Twenty minutes before done, make white sauce.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over medium heat. Add enough flour to make paste.
Add 4 cups milk slowly, stirring constantly. Cook until thick. Add 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour sauce over casserole when serving.

title: mercer children's everyday hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 8 patties. Heat frypan. Add patties and brown on both sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with raw vegetables.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Mix in chipped ham, cheese and other items.
Spread on hamburger rolls and put under broiler for 10 minutes.
Makes enough for 24 hamburger rolls.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: In saucepan, prepare noodles as label directs.
Drain and return noodles to pan.
Over medium-low heat, heat noodles, cream, margarine, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese until creamy. Toss well.
Use the remaining cheese to sprinkle each serving to taste.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into balls.
Place about 2-inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Remove immediately from pan.
Makes about 10 dozen, depending on size.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sheila's irish bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
With pastry blender, blend oleo.
Add by hand egg and milk.
Put layer of mix on bottom of loaf pan.
Cover with raisins and seed.
Poke raisins into dough.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix together the melted butter, sugar, egg, salt, flour, soda and vanilla.
Place into lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 320° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put small package of chocolate chips over when removed from oven.
When melted, spread over top. Chopped nuts can be added on top.
Kids love them.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add M&M's candies.
Drop from teaspoon onto floured cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat water, egg and vinegar, mixing well.
Add to flour mixture.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 (9-inch) crusts.

title: potato onion casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and onions.
Put a layer of potatoes in pan, then a layer of onions; alternate until gone.
Pour on soup and rinse can with water, pouring water in pan also.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons of Ranch dressing into cream cheese.
Spread evenly over taco shells.
Layer meat, cheese and spinach leaves, no stems (one layer only).
Roll up shell (like burrito).
Use cheese mixture on opposite side of shell while rolling to help hold together.
Slice 1-inch circles from end to end.
Use toothpicks to hold together if needed.
Can use dressing as dip.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Mix broccoli, ham, onion powder, salt, pepper, soups and 1 cup milk into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk and pour over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle parsley (optional).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown at 450°.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with dry stuffing mix.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil, milk and coffee.
Mix for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: basic quiche
directions: Sprinkle half of the cheese in the pie shell.
Top cheese with other fillings.
Beat together eggs, half and half and seasonings. Pour over filling and top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: connie's no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and milk; turn off.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour mixture over oats.
Mix well.
Put on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: shrimp `n' veggie alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute the peas, red pepper, carrots and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until crisp-tender; remove and keep warm.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Saute shrimp in oil until shrimp turn pink.
Return vegetables to pan; mix well.
Drain pasta.
Place pasta on six dinner plates.
Drizzle with Alfredo sauce and top with shrimp mixture.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Cool, then in large bowl, mix all together.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: spicy pumpkin bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In mixer bowl, beat eggs until frothy; beat in sugar and beat 2 minutes. Beat in oil and pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients over raisins or nuts and fold dry mixture into egg mixture. Do not overmix. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut into 4 squares.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls, 1 teaspoon dough in each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until slightly brown, in preheated 350° oven.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all well and press in dish with lid.
Can be frozen.

title: walnut rum balls
directions: Mix together and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered or granulated sugar.
Good to eat right away or later!
Store in light container.
Makes about 40.

title: fresh sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes in 1-inch chunks.
Core and cut unpeeled apples in 6 to 8 pieces.
Put sweet potatoes and apples in a large casserole dish with lid.
Dot with several pats of oleo. Add desired amount of sugar. Sprinkle with red hots and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: anne holsclaw's rainbow ice cream cake
directions: Thaw strawberries and mash.

Using tube pan or cake taker, place broken pieces of cake and ingredients as follows: Divide cake in 3 parts; mix dry gelatins with cake pieces into 3 bowls. Then mix strawberries with strawberry gelatin and cake mixture; oranges with orange gelatin and cake mixture; lime gelatin and crushed pineapple together.
Put in layers (pack down) and top each layer with ice cream.
Should be frozen overnight before cutting. Turn onto cake plate and serve immediately.
Keep frozen.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat; drain fat and set aside.
Blend mayo, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth. Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown on top, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Drop on a greased pan.
Cook at 450°.

title: do ahead potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll thin on board.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely; spread out, let dry.
Cut in strips and slice thin noodles.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding souffle
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add green pepper and saute for 1 minute until pepper is tender.
Stir in flour and slowly add half and half cream, whisking while cooking until mixture is very thick.
Stir in mustard, salt and cheese.
Blend in corn and egg yolks with the cheese mixture; set aside.
Whisk egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into cheese/corn mixture and blend thoroughly.
Turn into a buttered 1 to 2-quart casserole or souffle dish.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes or until golden and puffy.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: favorite blackberry cobbler(makes 9 servings)
directions: Combine blackberries, 1 cup sugar and cornstarch in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon into 9-inch square pan.
Combine margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, salt and vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in baking powder and flour.
Pour over blackberries and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: light caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt, butter and 1 cup half and half in a large heavy saucepan.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a full boil.
Gradually add remaining half and half so that the boiling does not stop.
Continue stirring to hard boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
When cold, turn out on cutting board and cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and gradually add sugar, creaming thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Alternately add sifted dry ingredients, applesauce and water. Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: vanilla kieffel
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla packet and vanilla extract. Mix thoroughly.
Add flour and nuts to mixture and mix together.
Take small pieces of dough and roll and shape into crescent shape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until it thickens.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well. Starting with crackers, make a layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan, then a layer of pudding mix.
Alternate, ending with crackers on top. Spread a thin layer of frosting on top. Refrigerate and cut in squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with sliced peaches.
Mix together butter, sugar, milk, flour and salt.
Pour batter over peaches. Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Add 1 cup water.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: witches' hat cookies(hungry little goblins will eat these up!)
directions: Roll out dough on board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake. Then you eat them!

title: hamburger cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Trim crust from 16 to 18 buttered bread slices.
Place slices, buttered side down in muffin tins.
Press into shape.
Fill with meat mixture (full). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: delicious cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; shape into ball.
Make a small well in the center of cheese ball.
Add strawberry preserves.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper. Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour, if possible.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line shallow pan with foil.
Cut wings in each joint; discard tips.
Melt butter in pan.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat. Place in pan and bake 25 minutes.
Turn and bake additional 20 to 25 minutes or until crisp.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: easy portuguese bean soup
directions: Simmer ham and sausage in water for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 15 minutes or until vegetables are done. Serve hot.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer cabbage and then other ingredients.
Repeat this process until all ingredients are used.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over this. Layer coconut, then chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Completely cool before cutting in small squares.
Very rich.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
When cold, remove from bones.
Put chicken in flat baking dish.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup; pour over chicken.
Melt margarine; mix with Ritz crumbs and poppy seed. Sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crisp cookies. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: toasted english muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, but English muffins.
Toast muffins.
Spread mixture on the toasted muffins.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Before serving, thaw for 15 minutes.
Cut each muffin into 4 pieces.
Broil until cheese melts, about 3 minutes. Watch them; they burn easily.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oleo.
Add ground beef, breaking it up as it browns.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles and cheese; bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour some tomato mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then add uncooked noodles.
Layer like lasagna.
Place cheese on top.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: german pancakes
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks and add flour, butter and salt; mix well.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into egg mixture.
Cook batter 1/8 at a time in butter in a large skillet.
When edges curl, turn and brown on the other side.
Spread with applesauce, jelly or other fruit sauce.
May also roll up and serve with sugar and butter.

title: diet orange congealed salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in refrigerator to jell.
Mix pudding mix with milk, then fold in Cool Whip and pour over jelled Jell-O.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together 30 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli-cheddar egg bake
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, beat eggs until mixed.
In a 2-quart glass measure, heat milk on High 1 1/2 to 4 minutes, until steaming.
Gradually beat into eggs.
Stir in bread and remaining ingredients, reserving 2 tablespoons cheese.
With spatula, lightly press bread mixture into egg mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: hot swiss mocha
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy until well blended.
Use one level tablespoon of mix with six ounces boiling water for each cup; stir well.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped cream.
Yields 16 (6 ounce) servings. Great for cold weather and coffee drinkers.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients; drop by tablespoon on hot griddle of skillet.
Flip when nearly done.
Serve immediately.

title: pikelets
directions: Mix egg and sugar until thick.
Add with milk to sifted flour, baking powder, and salt.
Lastly add melted butter.
Mix until smooth.
Drop by spoonful onto hot greased pan.
Fry like mini-pancakes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl measure 1/3 cup cocoa and remaining ingredients. With fork or wire whisk, beat just until blended.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake about 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan.
If you like, sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: chex party mix
directions: Mix butter, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into large plastic bag.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Seal top of bag.
Shake bag until all pieces are coated.
Pour into large bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Makes 9 cups.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix Bran, milk and sugar in another bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in eggs and applesauce.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until well blended.
Stir in thawed spinach, chopped water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover; chill for at least 2 hours.
Stir before serving with chips, vegetable sticks or spears.
Makes four cups.

title: summer cucumber walnut soup
directions: Shred enough of the cucumber to make 1/4 cup; set aside. Coarsely chop remaining cucumber and place in a blender or food processor.
Add yogurt and whirl until smooth.
Transfer mixture to a bowl and mix in reserved cucumber, walnuts, dill, garlic and oil.
Season to taste with salt.
Cover and refrigerate until cold (at least 1 hour).
Stir well.
Serve in chilled bowls.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: turkey piccata on grilled rolls
directions: Combine lemon juice, oil, 2 tablespoons capers with liquid, garlic and pepper in a shallow glass dish or large heavy plastic bag.
Add turkey; cover dish or close bag.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Remove turkey from marinade; discard marinade.
Oil hot grid to help prevent sticking.
Grill turkey on an uncovered grill over medium-hot Kingsford briquets until turkey is cooked through, turning once. Move cooked turkey slices to edge of grill to keep warm.
Grill rolls., cut side down, until roasted.
Add the last 4 ingredients, if desired.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Quarter the dates and place in a small saucepan.
Add water and sugar; cook until thickens.
Set aside to cool.
In second bowl, mix together flour, soda and salt.
Add sugar, oatmeal, melted butter and nuts.
Blend with fork until it becomes crumbly. Place crumbly mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Be sure to reserve 1 cup for the top.
Cover crumb mix with date mixture; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon fluff
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to mixture alternately with milk, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until done in center.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Use pastry blender to combine ingredients.
Form mixture into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Freeze on a cookie sheet. When frozen, remove from cookie sheet and store in a freezer Ziploc bag in the freezer.
Remove the amount you wish to bake and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve warm.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix everything in a saucepan until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add flavoring.
Pour in baked pie shells.

title: sinfully delicious chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan. As soon as it comes out of the oven, poke holes all over the cake with a fork or toothpick.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over the top of entire cake.
Next, pour entire jar of caramel over the cake.
Refrigerate.
When cool, top with Cool Whip and then broken up chunks of Heath candy bars.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cut top off of a large round loaf of bread,
unsliced.
Take	out
the insides of the bread and cut into
wedge
shaped
pieces.
Put
spinach	mixture in hollowed-out bread.
Place	wedged	pieces around the loaf and replace the top.
